1
00:00:05,226 --> 00:00:06,865
Episode 49

2
00:00:43,696 --> 00:00:45,227
What is it?

3
00:00:45,997 --> 00:00:48,466
You think with Lee Seokjin and some old

4
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:50,516
directors, you can turn the tables?

5
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,907
It's not that simple in the real world.

6
00:00:55,357 --> 00:00:57,547
Is that your way of doing things?

7
00:00:58,927 --> 00:01:01,506
Betraying a friend that trusts you,

8
00:01:01,507 --> 00:01:04,027
and stealing all of his money?

9
00:01:04,736 --> 00:01:07,716
Sangjun asked for this, do you know?

10
00:01:07,717 --> 00:01:09,506
Is that why you wanted my father to die?

11
00:01:09,507 --> 00:01:12,356
I said he was already
dead when I got there!

12
00:01:15,636 --> 00:01:16,956
Sure.

13
00:01:19,056 --> 00:01:22,195
Wherever you go and whomever you meet,

14
00:01:22,196 --> 00:01:23,996
keep telling that story.

15
00:01:24,946 --> 00:01:26,976
Even if

16
00:01:26,977 --> 00:01:30,286
you made my father die,

17
00:01:30,287 --> 00:01:32,415
don't ever speak of it.

18
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:34,037
Ever.

19
00:01:35,517 --> 00:01:38,097
If not,

20
00:01:38,776 --> 00:01:41,555
I would have to feel sorry for my father

21
00:01:41,556 --> 00:01:44,036
for being too foolish

22
00:01:44,037 --> 00:01:45,446
to have trusted you so much.

23
00:01:50,946 --> 00:01:53,037
It was for you.

24
00:01:55,207 --> 00:01:57,056
For you,

25
00:01:58,696 --> 00:02:01,227
for an ingrate like you,

26
00:02:03,517 --> 00:02:05,627
my father did all the work.

27
00:02:11,356 --> 00:02:14,505
From the beginning, my father prepared

28
00:02:14,506 --> 00:02:18,076
all the money and paperwork for you.

29
00:02:19,536 --> 00:02:22,845
Even if you hadn't stolen the money,

30
00:02:22,846 --> 00:02:26,225
if you just let things run its course,

31
00:02:26,226 --> 00:02:28,736
you would've eventually gotten all of it.

32
00:02:32,697 --> 00:02:36,495
I understand that you're an engineer,

33
00:02:36,496 --> 00:02:38,516
but what about running the company?

34
00:02:38,517 --> 00:02:41,155
Asking me to manage the money is...

35
00:02:41,156 --> 00:02:44,435
If you do it, it'll be like I'm doing it.

36
00:02:44,436 --> 00:02:45,696
Sangjun, still...

37
00:02:45,697 --> 00:02:47,505
On top of that,

38
00:02:47,506 --> 00:02:50,435
I don't know if I need to run the company.

39
00:02:50,436 --> 00:02:51,585
I want to hire someone capable,

40
00:02:51,586 --> 00:02:53,125
and have him run it the way he wants.

41
00:02:53,126 --> 00:02:54,886
I can focus on technology development,

42
00:02:54,887 --> 00:02:57,797
and he can help grow the company.

43
00:03:07,026 --> 00:03:07,857
(President Kim Sangjun)

44
00:03:07,858 --> 00:03:09,147
Sangjun.

45
00:03:09,547 --> 00:03:11,136
Sangjun!

46
00:03:11,137 --> 00:03:12,417
Hey, Sangjun!

47
00:03:40,026 --> 00:03:42,156
(Taehu Industry Stock
Certificate, $2.5 Million)

48
00:04:19,626 --> 00:04:23,816
Talk about lying through your teeth.

49
00:04:24,266 --> 00:04:26,515
Who in the world

50
00:04:26,516 --> 00:04:28,125
gives all his money to his friend

51
00:04:28,126 --> 00:04:30,616
when he has his own family,

52
00:04:30,617 --> 00:04:33,666
his own parents, and a wife?

53
00:04:33,667 --> 00:04:35,936
I don't understand, either.

54
00:04:37,436 --> 00:04:40,026
If he was alive, I'd love to ask him

55
00:04:41,657 --> 00:04:44,067
why he trusted someone like you.

56
00:04:45,766 --> 00:04:48,236
What kind of crazy idiot would

57
00:04:48,237 --> 00:04:51,787
trust his friend with all his money?

58
00:04:53,907 --> 00:04:57,327
You think I would believe that nonsense?

59
00:04:59,117 --> 00:05:01,277
Taehu Industry's attorney Hong Mungi.

60
00:05:03,237 --> 00:05:05,406
He was one of the people you fired

61
00:05:05,407 --> 00:05:07,877
when Taehu Industry filed for bankruptcy.

62
00:05:09,446 --> 00:05:11,396
You can ask him.

63
00:06:14,167 --> 00:06:16,977
(President Kim Sangjun)

64
00:06:17,136 --> 00:06:19,367
(Registration Certificate,
Owner Jang Taesu)

65
00:06:23,876 --> 00:06:26,426
Taesu, what time will you be back?

66
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:29,895
Well, I think I'll finish around 5.

67
00:06:29,896 --> 00:06:31,765
I'll see you then.

68
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:34,305
I have something to tell you.

69
00:06:34,306 --> 00:06:36,046
What is it? Tell me now.

70
00:06:36,047 --> 00:06:36,967
I'll tell you later.

71
00:06:36,968 --> 00:06:38,546
Don't be late.

72
00:06:38,547 --> 00:06:41,625
I have a favor to ask you,

73
00:06:41,626 --> 00:06:44,086
and something to give you.

74
00:07:22,237 --> 00:07:24,326
Your mother's waiting.

75
00:07:33,427 --> 00:07:36,075
If

76
00:07:36,076 --> 00:07:38,836
Anything happens to me,

77
00:07:38,837 --> 00:07:40,597
ask Taesu for help.

78
00:07:43,287 --> 00:07:45,566
Don't say such a thing.

79
00:07:46,756 --> 00:07:48,456
I'm saying, just in case.

80
00:08:03,646 --> 00:08:05,106
Hello?

81
00:08:15,227 --> 00:08:18,517
Who is this, so early in the morning?

82
00:08:20,737 --> 00:08:22,576
Do you remember me?

83
00:08:24,016 --> 00:08:25,276
President Jang!

84
00:08:26,427 --> 00:08:27,716
- Come in. / - No, no, wait.

85
00:08:27,717 --> 00:08:29,527
My coming in isn't important right now.

86
00:08:29,857 --> 00:08:34,395
Did you meet Sangjun's son Kim Jiwan?

87
00:08:34,396 --> 00:08:35,966
Did you see him a few days ago?

88
00:08:35,967 --> 00:08:40,337
Yes, I met Jiwan a few days ago.

89
00:08:41,166 --> 00:08:43,716
What did you two talk about?

90
00:08:44,376 --> 00:08:47,306
He asked about the financial state

91
00:08:47,307 --> 00:08:50,966
of Mr. Kim when he passed away.

92
00:08:50,967 --> 00:08:56,237
Is there any legal problems?

93
00:08:57,827 --> 00:08:59,226
Yes,

94
00:08:59,227 --> 00:09:01,535
when Sangjun died,

95
00:09:01,536 --> 00:09:03,655
what happened to his assets?

96
00:09:03,656 --> 00:09:07,196
You know that better than I do.

97
00:09:07,197 --> 00:09:10,255
He turned everything into cash,

98
00:09:10,256 --> 00:09:12,966
and invested it into his company.

99
00:09:12,967 --> 00:09:14,236
Invested it,

100
00:09:14,237 --> 00:09:15,515
yes.

101
00:09:15,516 --> 00:09:16,846
Yes, that's right.

102
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:18,255
He invested all of it.

103
00:09:18,256 --> 00:09:20,466
He didn't plan on giving it to me, right?

104
00:09:20,467 --> 00:09:27,645
He said he was making you the president.

105
00:09:27,646 --> 00:09:32,087
Isn't that the same thing?

106
00:09:40,087 --> 00:09:44,856
I want to give Taesu a chance.

107
00:09:44,857 --> 00:09:46,405
I want to make it

108
00:09:46,406 --> 00:09:49,165
so that he can make this company grow.

109
00:09:49,166 --> 00:09:50,836
Mr. Kim,

110
00:09:50,837 --> 00:09:53,457
what about your family?

111
00:09:54,067 --> 00:09:57,897
Putting him in charge of the money is...

112
00:09:58,766 --> 00:10:01,806
This investment is for my family.

113
00:10:01,807 --> 00:10:03,377
Excuse me?

114
00:10:05,197 --> 00:10:07,275
I'm not sure

115
00:10:07,276 --> 00:10:09,556
how much longer

116
00:10:09,557 --> 00:10:11,357
my heart will last.

117
00:10:12,727 --> 00:10:16,706
Without me, what will happen to my mother,

118
00:10:16,707 --> 00:10:18,217
my wife, and kids?

119
00:10:19,987 --> 00:10:22,745
Anyone can talk my mother into signing

120
00:10:22,746 --> 00:10:25,306
any document they want, and my wife

121
00:10:25,307 --> 00:10:29,366
does not know how to deal with my mother.

122
00:10:29,367 --> 00:10:33,885
I need someone to be there for my family.

123
00:10:33,886 --> 00:10:37,255
Money aside, I know Taesu will

124
00:10:37,256 --> 00:10:40,056
take great care of my family.

125
00:10:41,276 --> 00:10:45,796
I know what kind of man he is.

126
00:10:54,437 --> 00:10:57,297
President Jang...

127
00:11:01,516 --> 00:11:03,686
You,

128
00:11:03,687 --> 00:11:05,456
you're lying, aren't you?

129
00:11:05,457 --> 00:11:06,696
How much money did Kim Jiwan give you?

130
00:11:06,697 --> 00:11:08,387
How much did it take to pay you off?

131
00:11:08,388 --> 00:11:09,896
President Jang...

132
00:11:24,496 --> 00:11:26,875
I need to see you right now.

133
00:11:26,876 --> 00:11:28,175
Come to my office.

134
00:11:28,176 --> 00:11:30,415
I'm not interested in seeing you.

135
00:11:30,416 --> 00:11:31,746
I'm hanging up.

136
00:11:38,156 --> 00:11:39,607
Take me to Kim Jiwan's apartment.

137
00:12:10,266 --> 00:12:12,175
I just

138
00:12:12,176 --> 00:12:15,586
met with Taehu Industry's company lawyer.

139
00:12:17,577 --> 00:12:19,356
Then you must've heard everything.

140
00:12:19,357 --> 00:12:20,786
Yes.

141
00:12:23,006 --> 00:12:27,636
You mean you heard about Sangjun?

142
00:12:28,557 --> 00:12:31,736
Your family's become quite crafty.

143
00:12:31,737 --> 00:12:33,505
Was it money, or something else?

144
00:12:33,506 --> 00:12:36,795
How did you make him lie to me like that?

145
00:12:36,796 --> 00:12:39,236
I remember him as a man of integrity,

146
00:12:39,237 --> 00:12:41,227
so how did you buy him off?

147
00:12:43,766 --> 00:12:47,616
You're well-prepared to taint my name.

148
00:12:47,617 --> 00:12:50,175
Turning Sangjun into a saint

149
00:12:50,176 --> 00:12:52,566
will make me look dirtier and pettier.

150
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:54,007
On top of stealing money, I'd become

151
00:12:54,008 --> 00:12:58,056
a bastard who betrayed his best friend.

152
00:12:58,057 --> 00:13:00,096
Is that the plan?

153
00:13:00,097 --> 00:13:02,645
Telling the world how dirty and petty I am?

154
00:13:02,646 --> 00:13:05,036
That's what you're afraid of?

155
00:13:08,477 --> 00:13:10,665
I'm relieved.

156
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:14,096
At least you know what you did was wrong.

157
00:13:18,526 --> 00:13:20,717
Why did you do it?

158
00:13:22,756 --> 00:13:25,467
You're not that type of person.

159
00:13:26,276 --> 00:13:28,706
You valued people,

160
00:13:28,707 --> 00:13:31,277
and you were very understanding.

161
00:13:32,817 --> 00:13:36,326
So Sangjun, Mother, and I

162
00:13:36,327 --> 00:13:39,635
trusted you with everything.

163
00:13:39,636 --> 00:13:42,347
You were upright and kindhearted.

164
00:13:45,737 --> 00:13:47,817
What happened to you?

165
00:13:49,916 --> 00:13:54,326
How did you end up here like this,

166
00:13:54,327 --> 00:13:58,957
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

167
00:14:09,146 --> 00:14:11,836
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

168
00:14:11,837 --> 00:14:13,316
bought that lawyer off.

169
00:14:13,317 --> 00:14:14,476
Taesu, what if...

170
00:14:14,477 --> 00:14:16,045
What if, what?

171
00:14:16,046 --> 00:14:17,905
You think it might be true?

172
00:14:17,906 --> 00:14:19,826
But if it's true, I'm...

173
00:14:24,967 --> 00:14:26,545
No.

174
00:14:26,546 --> 00:14:29,706
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

175
00:14:29,707 --> 00:14:32,885
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

176
00:14:32,886 --> 00:14:33,696
Wait...

177
00:14:33,697 --> 00:14:35,236
Wait, this means

178
00:14:35,237 --> 00:14:38,307
he can buy my people off, too.

179
00:14:39,727 --> 00:14:42,457
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

180
00:14:43,467 --> 00:14:44,756
Yes, sir.

181
00:14:54,467 --> 00:14:57,167
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

182
00:14:58,046 --> 00:14:59,106
I'm Kim Jiwan.

183
00:14:59,107 --> 00:15:00,406
Have a seat.

184
00:15:05,227 --> 00:15:08,716
I heard the news from a former employee.

185
00:15:08,717 --> 00:15:11,096
You've been contacting former directors?

186
00:15:11,097 --> 00:15:12,556
How many people have you met with?

187
00:15:12,557 --> 00:15:14,167
About twenty.

188
00:15:15,036 --> 00:15:16,816
And I've been preparing

189
00:15:16,817 --> 00:15:18,775
the recordings of their accounts.

190
00:15:18,776 --> 00:15:20,135
I think I can report the story right away

191
00:15:20,136 --> 00:15:22,895
if I had a copy of those recordings.

192
00:15:22,896 --> 00:15:25,245
Can you give me a copy?

193
00:15:25,246 --> 00:15:26,505
Of course.

194
00:15:26,506 --> 00:15:28,847
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

195
00:16:31,057 --> 00:16:33,657
Can't fall asleep?

196
00:16:36,176 --> 00:16:38,676
I can't seem to understand Father.

197
00:16:40,176 --> 00:16:43,635
Why did he try to put someone like

198
00:16:43,636 --> 00:16:46,276
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

199
00:16:48,107 --> 00:16:49,316
That was so foolish.

200
00:16:49,317 --> 00:16:50,697
Jiwan.

201
00:16:52,837 --> 00:16:55,477
Don't blame your father.

202
00:16:56,036 --> 00:16:59,505
Back then, the only person he could trust

203
00:16:59,506 --> 00:17:02,046
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

204
00:17:03,197 --> 00:17:06,476
With his health deteriorating,

205
00:17:06,477 --> 00:17:10,066
your father was afraid of the future.

206
00:17:10,727 --> 00:17:13,456
And he thought

207
00:17:13,457 --> 00:17:18,025
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

208
00:17:18,026 --> 00:17:20,197
He was wrong.

209
00:17:20,987 --> 00:17:23,035
He trusted the man

210
00:17:23,036 --> 00:17:25,676
who stole all his money the day he died.

211
00:17:25,677 --> 00:17:28,535
If it were me,

212
00:17:28,536 --> 00:17:30,286
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

213
00:17:31,667 --> 00:17:34,555
He was a different man

214
00:17:34,556 --> 00:17:36,765
from who he is now.

215
00:17:36,766 --> 00:17:38,815
And that's why I can't forgive him.

216
00:17:38,816 --> 00:17:40,896
As a human being,

217
00:17:40,897 --> 00:17:42,037
you cannot betray someone

218
00:17:42,038 --> 00:17:43,856
who trusts you.

219
00:19:28,717 --> 00:19:30,487
Hyeondo.

220
00:19:32,727 --> 00:19:37,147
Why not resign from your father's company?

221
00:19:41,116 --> 00:19:45,496
I'll look into another job for you.

222
00:19:49,227 --> 00:19:51,107
I should go to work.

223
00:20:01,996 --> 00:20:04,245
Sugyeong came to see you?

224
00:20:04,246 --> 00:20:07,667
She really begged for your forgiveness?

225
00:20:08,776 --> 00:20:12,106
Sugyeong looked really bad.

226
00:20:13,217 --> 00:20:15,476
I think she's miserable.

227
00:20:15,477 --> 00:20:17,025
She should be.

228
00:20:17,026 --> 00:20:18,476
Of course.

229
00:20:18,477 --> 00:20:21,586
If she's not, she's not human.

230
00:20:22,276 --> 00:20:25,906
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

231
00:20:25,907 --> 00:20:27,477
What?

232
00:20:28,227 --> 00:20:31,605
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

233
00:20:31,606 --> 00:20:33,956
Oh, my.

234
00:20:33,957 --> 00:20:36,207
You sure are a saint.

235
00:20:36,856 --> 00:20:38,706
She's going through a rough time after

236
00:20:38,707 --> 00:20:41,966
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

237
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:45,227
You're the one I feel sorry for.

238
00:20:46,276 --> 00:20:51,805
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

239
00:20:51,806 --> 00:20:53,605
He's at the hospital.

240
00:20:53,606 --> 00:20:55,626
Hyeondo?

241
00:20:55,627 --> 00:20:57,245
How could a child be healthy

242
00:20:57,246 --> 00:20:59,575
when his parents have no morals?

243
00:20:59,576 --> 00:21:03,346
Karma passes down to children.

244
00:21:06,137 --> 00:21:09,847
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

245
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:11,976
How could I say no to you?

246
00:21:11,977 --> 00:21:14,285
I had to do it.

247
00:21:14,286 --> 00:21:15,676
So I was thinking,

248
00:21:15,677 --> 00:21:17,605
I heard you might end up

249
00:21:17,606 --> 00:21:20,416
taking over the company.

250
00:21:20,417 --> 00:21:22,686
There's an idea

251
00:21:22,687 --> 00:21:26,206
I've been developing for five years,

252
00:21:26,207 --> 00:21:29,025
and going to Russia gave me

253
00:21:29,026 --> 00:21:31,095
reaffirmation on my idea.

254
00:21:31,096 --> 00:21:33,515
So I was wondering

255
00:21:33,516 --> 00:21:36,765
if you could give me a chance

256
00:21:36,766 --> 00:21:39,217
to present that idea to you.

257
00:21:43,096 --> 00:21:44,796
Please don't joke around with me.

258
00:21:45,487 --> 00:21:46,946
I'm not...

259
00:21:46,947 --> 00:21:50,626
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

260
00:21:50,627 --> 00:21:52,706
and made your life difficult.

261
00:21:52,707 --> 00:21:56,646
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

262
00:21:56,647 --> 00:21:58,676
yes, like in Chinese novels,

263
00:21:58,677 --> 00:22:00,226
in order to make someone a hero,

264
00:22:00,227 --> 00:22:02,305
people around him

265
00:22:02,306 --> 00:22:05,095
create hardships for him.

266
00:22:05,096 --> 00:22:07,045
All Chinese heroes are like that.

267
00:22:07,046 --> 00:22:09,176
They prevail over and over again,

268
00:22:09,177 --> 00:22:10,167
and accomplish...

269
00:22:10,168 --> 00:22:11,765
It's okay.

270
00:22:11,766 --> 00:22:12,697
No, I...

271
00:22:12,698 --> 00:22:14,737
I said it's okay!

272
00:22:15,407 --> 00:22:16,716
Why do you keep bugging me!

273
00:22:16,717 --> 00:22:18,216
I said it's okay!

274
00:22:18,217 --> 00:22:19,756
Something great.

275
00:22:22,106 --> 00:22:23,436
I think you're mistaken.

276
00:22:23,437 --> 00:22:24,896
It's okay.

277
00:22:24,897 --> 00:22:27,256
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

278
00:22:27,826 --> 00:22:29,216
No, I'm not mistaken.

279
00:22:29,217 --> 00:22:31,176
I think you're mistaken.

280
00:22:31,177 --> 00:22:34,046
It's not like that. Just think about it.

281
00:22:34,526 --> 00:22:37,355
When you asked me for a favor like that,

282
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:41,126
wasn't it because we are close?

283
00:22:42,167 --> 00:22:43,795
- Yes. / - Right?

284
00:22:43,796 --> 00:22:49,355
So since we share a special relationship,

285
00:22:49,356 --> 00:22:50,326
let me present it in a special...

286
00:22:50,327 --> 00:22:51,436
Jiwan.

287
00:22:51,846 --> 00:22:52,916
Hi, Eunsu.

288
00:22:52,917 --> 00:22:54,245
Ms. Han Eunsu!

289
00:22:54,246 --> 00:22:56,345
Oh? Hello.

290
00:22:56,346 --> 00:22:57,836
What are you doing here?

291
00:23:00,066 --> 00:23:01,636
Huh?

292
00:23:03,707 --> 00:23:05,727
She's my little sister.

293
00:23:06,727 --> 00:23:08,245
Your real sister?

294
00:23:08,246 --> 00:23:09,366
Yes.

295
00:23:09,687 --> 00:23:14,317
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

296
00:23:15,957 --> 00:23:17,505
Jiwan, Eunsu.

297
00:23:17,506 --> 00:23:19,397
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

298
00:23:19,987 --> 00:23:20,995
Remember?

299
00:23:20,996 --> 00:23:23,686
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

300
00:23:23,687 --> 00:23:25,075
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

301
00:23:25,076 --> 00:23:26,036
Oh, Aunt.

302
00:23:26,037 --> 00:23:29,576
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

303
00:23:31,096 --> 00:23:32,146
Hi.

304
00:23:32,147 --> 00:23:35,396
I'm Park Haengsuk.

305
00:23:35,397 --> 00:23:36,615
Excuse me?

306
00:23:36,616 --> 00:23:38,456
Park...

307
00:23:38,457 --> 00:23:42,237
You're his aunt, but
your last name is Park?

308
00:23:43,967 --> 00:23:49,285
Kim, Han and Park.

309
00:23:49,286 --> 00:23:51,906
A family with different last names?

310
00:23:57,246 --> 00:23:59,876
What happened?

311
00:23:59,877 --> 00:24:01,456
Why is that office empty?

312
00:24:01,457 --> 00:24:04,176
All the desks and chairs are gone.

313
00:24:04,177 --> 00:24:05,775
Oh, that office?

314
00:24:05,776 --> 00:24:07,275
They moved out.

315
00:24:07,276 --> 00:24:09,025
They moved out?

316
00:24:09,026 --> 00:24:11,206
Where did they go?

317
00:24:11,207 --> 00:24:12,926
Where are my daughter and husband?

318
00:24:12,927 --> 00:24:17,927
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

319
00:24:20,727 --> 00:24:22,276
A, a tent?

320
00:24:29,137 --> 00:24:30,255
Oh,

321
00:24:30,256 --> 00:24:33,745
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

322
00:24:33,746 --> 00:24:35,025
When is the phone guy coming?

323
00:24:35,026 --> 00:24:36,886
He'll be here at 3.

324
00:24:36,887 --> 00:24:38,876
Where should the line go?

325
00:24:38,877 --> 00:24:40,387
I'll find a spot.

326
00:24:40,766 --> 00:24:42,076
I'll take that, Yeongju.

327
00:24:49,167 --> 00:24:51,216
You shouldn't bite off
more than you can chew,

328
00:24:51,217 --> 00:24:52,847
and mingle with your own kind!

329
00:24:52,848 --> 00:24:56,045
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

330
00:24:56,046 --> 00:24:57,946
It's my fault for signing a contract

331
00:24:57,947 --> 00:25:00,515
that says the owner can
evict us at any time.

332
00:25:00,516 --> 00:25:02,226
How dare you side with Jiwan!

333
00:25:02,227 --> 00:25:04,197
I'm going to get him for this!

334
00:25:05,326 --> 00:25:06,436
Honey, Mi...

335
00:25:09,796 --> 00:25:11,346
What did Mom say?

336
00:25:13,086 --> 00:25:15,986
She's going to get Jiwan.

337
00:25:15,987 --> 00:25:17,296
What?

338
00:25:18,076 --> 00:25:19,016
Seriously...

339
00:25:19,017 --> 00:25:20,346
Let's hurry up.

340
00:25:24,306 --> 00:25:25,796
Jiwan, you!

341
00:25:26,036 --> 00:25:26,906
Hello.

342
00:25:26,907 --> 00:25:28,207
Just a second.

343
00:25:28,647 --> 00:25:29,917
Hello.

344
00:25:30,697 --> 00:25:33,457
It's an important meeting. This way.

345
00:25:33,907 --> 00:25:35,976
Everything looks great.

346
00:25:35,977 --> 00:25:39,676
I can see, now that I'm here.

347
00:25:39,677 --> 00:25:43,305
You put up a makeshift
office near the farm.

348
00:25:43,306 --> 00:25:47,186
It shows your concern for quality control.

349
00:25:47,187 --> 00:25:48,476
I just need to sign here, yes?

350
00:25:48,477 --> 00:25:49,877
Yes.

351
00:25:55,356 --> 00:25:56,525
Thank you.

352
00:25:56,526 --> 00:25:57,496
I hope this works out great.

353
00:25:57,497 --> 00:25:58,526
Thank you.

354
00:26:04,187 --> 00:26:05,245
Goodbye.

355
00:26:05,246 --> 00:26:07,525
That guy

356
00:26:07,526 --> 00:26:09,226
is great at many things.

357
00:26:09,227 --> 00:26:11,075
He's amazing.

358
00:26:11,076 --> 00:26:13,496
He performs better under pressure.

359
00:26:14,877 --> 00:26:17,386
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

360
00:26:17,387 --> 00:26:18,817
And it's such a hot day.

361
00:26:18,818 --> 00:26:21,396
Let me get you something cool to drink.

362
00:26:21,397 --> 00:26:22,717
Mr. Jang.

363
00:26:28,806 --> 00:26:30,816
This is worth $30,000.

364
00:26:35,346 --> 00:26:38,716
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

365
00:26:38,717 --> 00:26:40,505
Hey, cut me some slack.

366
00:26:40,506 --> 00:26:41,916
I was caught off guard.

367
00:26:41,917 --> 00:26:43,245
It slipped out.

368
00:26:43,246 --> 00:26:44,536
I can't believe you.

369
00:26:44,836 --> 00:26:47,686
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

370
00:26:48,967 --> 00:26:50,085
Director, you're here.

371
00:26:50,086 --> 00:26:51,495
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

372
00:26:51,496 --> 00:26:52,856
Yes.

373
00:26:54,056 --> 00:26:55,346
What are you doing here?

374
00:26:55,897 --> 00:26:57,295
What do you think?

375
00:26:57,296 --> 00:26:59,115
They are working so hard on a hot day,

376
00:26:59,116 --> 00:27:00,636
so I bought them Korean pork

377
00:27:00,637 --> 00:27:03,236
to help them restore some energy.

378
00:27:03,237 --> 00:27:06,115
Domestic is always the best.

379
00:27:06,116 --> 00:27:08,506
Of course. You're a wise man.

380
00:27:10,046 --> 00:27:12,706
Honey, don't just stand there.
Come and sit.

381
00:27:12,707 --> 00:27:14,315
- Come here. / - Yeongju,
come and sit down.

382
00:27:14,316 --> 00:27:15,785
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

383
00:27:15,786 --> 00:27:16,886
Let me go get some more lettuce.

384
00:27:16,887 --> 00:27:18,097
Okay.

385
00:27:24,316 --> 00:27:25,525
Wait,

386
00:27:25,526 --> 00:27:27,686
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

387
00:27:27,687 --> 00:27:29,035
What's going on?

388
00:27:29,036 --> 00:27:30,315
Oh, I can't believe you.

389
00:27:30,316 --> 00:27:32,376
When? People might actually believe that.

390
00:27:32,377 --> 00:27:34,476
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

391
00:27:34,477 --> 00:27:37,946
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

392
00:27:37,947 --> 00:27:40,736
so I bought him Korean pork,

393
00:27:40,737 --> 00:27:42,676
to help him restore energy.

394
00:27:42,677 --> 00:27:45,136
Why are you just sitting there?

395
00:27:45,137 --> 00:27:46,916
Go and help wash the lettuce.

396
00:27:46,917 --> 00:27:48,107
Go help Jiwan.

397
00:27:48,556 --> 00:27:50,026
Okay.

398
00:27:51,677 --> 00:27:55,456
I'm a great judge of character.

399
00:27:55,457 --> 00:27:59,265
Mom, just have one spoonful.

400
00:27:59,266 --> 00:28:00,136
Say ah.

401
00:28:00,137 --> 00:28:03,115
I don't want any chicken porridge.

402
00:28:03,116 --> 00:28:06,045
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

403
00:28:06,046 --> 00:28:08,545
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

404
00:28:08,546 --> 00:28:11,216
so you can restore energy, okay?

405
00:28:11,217 --> 00:28:13,436
Just have one spoonful.

406
00:28:13,437 --> 00:28:14,567
Say ah.

407
00:28:20,496 --> 00:28:22,416
See?

408
00:28:22,417 --> 00:28:25,305
You're upset because of what you said.

409
00:28:25,306 --> 00:28:27,726
I didn't say anything wrong.

410
00:28:27,727 --> 00:28:31,085
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

411
00:28:31,086 --> 00:28:34,026
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

412
00:28:35,737 --> 00:28:37,406
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

413
00:28:37,407 --> 00:28:39,857
and meets someone nice.

414
00:28:40,816 --> 00:28:43,136
I'm sure she will.

415
00:28:43,727 --> 00:28:46,397
Couples form and break up all the time.

416
00:28:48,526 --> 00:28:51,595
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

417
00:28:51,596 --> 00:28:54,846
Jiwan has no time for that.

418
00:28:56,987 --> 00:28:58,197
This?

419
00:29:01,496 --> 00:29:02,996
You see,

420
00:29:03,477 --> 00:29:07,107
here are the size and unit.

421
00:29:10,366 --> 00:29:12,346
Hi.

422
00:29:14,657 --> 00:29:17,867
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

423
00:29:18,167 --> 00:29:20,317
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

424
00:29:20,318 --> 00:29:21,996
But why are you here?

425
00:29:24,437 --> 00:29:26,876
Oh, I'm stuffed.

426
00:29:26,877 --> 00:29:30,755
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

427
00:29:30,756 --> 00:29:32,236
You ate a lot of it.

428
00:29:32,237 --> 00:29:33,737
Because it was delicious.

429
00:29:36,697 --> 00:29:39,825
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

430
00:29:39,826 --> 00:29:41,946
It's okay. I can go home alone.

431
00:29:42,377 --> 00:29:43,297
Don't say that.

432
00:29:43,298 --> 00:29:45,575
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

433
00:29:45,576 --> 00:29:46,676
Take her home.

434
00:29:46,677 --> 00:29:48,186
No, that's not going to happen.

435
00:29:48,187 --> 00:29:49,745
Don't say that. Just go.

436
00:29:49,746 --> 00:29:51,315
What are you two doing?

437
00:29:51,316 --> 00:29:52,716
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

438
00:29:52,717 --> 00:29:54,626
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

439
00:29:54,627 --> 00:29:55,906
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

440
00:29:55,907 --> 00:29:56,867
Okay.

441
00:29:56,868 --> 00:29:58,226
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

442
00:30:10,137 --> 00:30:12,267
Are those two dating?

443
00:30:12,957 --> 00:30:15,075
They're not together yet,

444
00:30:15,076 --> 00:30:17,996
but they are testing the waters.

445
00:30:19,816 --> 00:30:22,495
It's frustrating to watch them.

446
00:30:22,496 --> 00:30:24,127
Yeongju...

447
00:30:24,856 --> 00:30:26,285
She's nice.

448
00:30:26,286 --> 00:30:27,626
She is.

449
00:30:27,627 --> 00:30:29,815
She's pretty and pleasant.

450
00:30:29,816 --> 00:30:33,065
And she's a teacher.

451
00:30:33,066 --> 00:30:34,216
Don't you think they look good together?

452
00:30:34,217 --> 00:30:35,907
Yes, they do.

453
00:30:46,356 --> 00:30:47,576
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

454
00:31:11,927 --> 00:31:14,456
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

455
00:31:14,457 --> 00:31:16,316
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

456
00:31:18,006 --> 00:31:19,586
I'm just practicing.

457
00:31:19,996 --> 00:31:21,536
Practicing?

458
00:31:25,187 --> 00:31:27,355
Oh, I get it.

459
00:31:27,356 --> 00:31:28,386
Girl...

460
00:31:28,387 --> 00:31:31,775
You have a good eye.

461
00:31:31,776 --> 00:31:32,586
What do you mean?

462
00:31:32,587 --> 00:31:34,466
Jiwan.

463
00:31:34,467 --> 00:31:36,146
Who cares about education?

464
00:31:36,147 --> 00:31:39,646
To me, money trumps everything.

465
00:31:39,647 --> 00:31:42,647
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

466
00:31:45,167 --> 00:31:47,005
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

467
00:31:47,006 --> 00:31:49,285
Eunsu is easy.

468
00:31:49,286 --> 00:31:52,717
The grandmother-in-law
will become forgetful.

469
00:31:53,326 --> 00:31:57,265
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

470
00:31:57,266 --> 00:31:59,156
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

471
00:31:59,157 --> 00:32:00,515
I told you it's not like that.

472
00:32:00,516 --> 00:32:01,386
Just leave me alone.

473
00:32:01,387 --> 00:32:04,275
How could I leave you alone?

474
00:32:04,276 --> 00:32:05,926
You won't go on blind dates,

475
00:32:05,927 --> 00:32:08,256
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

476
00:32:09,306 --> 00:32:10,795
If it were me in the old days,

477
00:32:10,796 --> 00:32:12,717
I would've already...

478
00:32:13,467 --> 00:32:15,186
What's the use of giving you my looks?

479
00:32:15,187 --> 00:32:16,835
Just look at yourself.

480
00:32:16,836 --> 00:32:19,916
You're dressed like a tomboy,

481
00:32:19,917 --> 00:32:21,797
and you haven't taken a shower.

482
00:32:21,798 --> 00:32:24,745
You need to make yourself look pretty!

483
00:32:24,746 --> 00:32:27,436
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

484
00:32:27,437 --> 00:32:29,936
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

485
00:32:29,937 --> 00:32:31,406
You have to look pretty!

486
00:32:31,407 --> 00:32:33,265
What good will cooking do for you?

487
00:32:33,266 --> 00:32:34,636
Besides your pretty face,

488
00:32:34,637 --> 00:32:37,386
you got nothing from me!

489
00:32:37,387 --> 00:32:39,697
What do you mean? Like this?

490
00:32:42,657 --> 00:32:43,827
Oh, you're impossible.

491
00:32:43,828 --> 00:32:46,275
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

492
00:32:46,276 --> 00:32:49,146
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

493
00:32:51,727 --> 00:32:52,795
Minja.

494
00:32:52,796 --> 00:32:53,717
Oh!

495
00:32:53,717 --> 00:32:54,687
Ms. Lee!

496
00:32:54,688 --> 00:32:55,736
What are you doing here?

497
00:32:55,737 --> 00:32:59,035
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

498
00:32:59,036 --> 00:33:00,526
What about you?

499
00:33:01,167 --> 00:33:04,016
Yeongju's been complaining
about neck pain, too.

500
00:33:05,306 --> 00:33:06,585
Well,

501
00:33:06,586 --> 00:33:10,196
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

502
00:33:11,677 --> 00:33:13,005
I've given up on that.

503
00:33:13,006 --> 00:33:14,355
How they feel about each
other is important,

504
00:33:14,356 --> 00:33:16,086
not their background.

505
00:33:16,536 --> 00:33:19,345
You're right!

506
00:33:19,346 --> 00:33:24,526
But I heard you hold education very high.

507
00:33:25,407 --> 00:33:28,696
If they're in love,
education doesn't matter.

508
00:33:28,697 --> 00:33:31,737
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

509
00:33:32,477 --> 00:33:37,596
But isn't a small family better?

510
00:33:38,427 --> 00:33:41,765
I would prefer a small family,

511
00:33:41,766 --> 00:33:43,166
but these days, as complicated as it is,

512
00:33:43,167 --> 00:33:46,456
people don't live with married children.

513
00:33:46,457 --> 00:33:48,877
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

514
00:33:50,016 --> 00:33:51,575
But that's...

515
00:33:51,576 --> 00:33:53,416
Well...

516
00:33:53,417 --> 00:33:55,785
Old people don't live forever.

517
00:33:55,786 --> 00:33:58,487
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

518
00:33:59,016 --> 00:34:01,535
I'm not going to let my daughter

519
00:34:01,536 --> 00:34:03,345
date anyone with a large family.

520
00:34:03,346 --> 00:34:05,755
What if she gets stuck with them?

521
00:34:05,756 --> 00:34:07,576
That won't be good.

522
00:34:09,207 --> 00:34:12,386
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

523
00:34:12,727 --> 00:34:14,495
As long as they live separately,

524
00:34:14,496 --> 00:34:17,066
you don't mind a big family?

525
00:34:17,067 --> 00:34:18,615
Of course not.

526
00:34:18,616 --> 00:34:20,917
As long as they are in love.

527
00:34:21,797 --> 00:34:22,687
Why do you ask?

528
00:34:22,688 --> 00:34:26,476
You have someone in mind?

529
00:34:26,477 --> 00:34:27,926
Of course.

530
00:34:29,746 --> 00:34:31,906
- You do? / - Yes.

531
00:34:43,076 --> 00:34:45,845
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

532
00:34:45,846 --> 00:34:49,606
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

533
00:34:49,607 --> 00:34:52,646
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

534
00:34:52,647 --> 00:34:55,856
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

535
00:34:55,857 --> 00:34:57,436
There are protocols for reporters...

536
00:34:57,437 --> 00:34:59,026
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

537
00:34:59,027 --> 00:35:01,745
former directors will be giving statements!

538
00:35:01,746 --> 00:35:03,135
Tell me if it's true,

539
00:35:03,136 --> 00:35:05,385
or if it's slander!

540
00:35:05,386 --> 00:35:08,296
President Jang!

541
00:35:08,297 --> 00:35:09,417
Please leave.

542
00:35:12,727 --> 00:35:14,757
Refuse all interviews.

543
00:35:15,377 --> 00:35:16,917
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

544
00:35:17,806 --> 00:35:20,245
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

545
00:35:20,246 --> 00:35:22,286
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

546
00:35:24,156 --> 00:35:25,385
If he had all the evidence,

547
00:35:25,386 --> 00:35:27,506
he would've written about it already.

548
00:35:28,266 --> 00:35:30,756
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

549
00:35:30,757 --> 00:35:34,106
I told you to find him, by any means!

550
00:35:34,107 --> 00:35:34,947
What are you doing?

551
00:35:34,948 --> 00:35:36,776
Is it that you can't or won't?

552
00:35:39,136 --> 00:35:40,856
Seokjin was

553
00:35:40,857 --> 00:35:43,595
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

554
00:35:43,596 --> 00:35:45,596
and is still with us today.

555
00:35:46,676 --> 00:35:49,885
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

556
00:35:49,886 --> 00:35:52,296
whenever we reach a new milestone.

557
00:35:53,687 --> 00:35:57,546
Hyeokju practically lived with us

558
00:35:57,547 --> 00:35:59,227
at the factory.

559
