when Sangjun died,

840
01:09:44,247 --> 01:09:46,366
what happened to his assets?

841
01:09:46,367 --> 01:09:49,906
You know that better than I do.

842
01:09:49,907 --> 01:09:52,965
He turned everything into cash,

843
01:09:52,966 --> 01:09:55,675
and invested it into his company.

844
01:09:55,676 --> 01:09:56,946
Invested it,

845
01:09:56,947 --> 01:09:58,226
yes.

846
01:09:58,227 --> 01:09:59,555
Yes, that's right.

847
01:09:59,556 --> 01:10:00,965
He invested all of it.

848
01:10:00,966 --> 01:10:03,175
He didn't plan on giving it to me, right?

849
01:10:03,176 --> 01:10:10,356
He said he was making you the president.

850
01:10:10,357 --> 01:10:14,796
Isn't that the same thing?

851
01:10:22,796 --> 01:10:27,566
I want to give Taesu a chance.

852
01:10:27,567 --> 01:10:29,116
I want to make it

853
01:10:29,117 --> 01:10:31,875
so that he can make this company grow.

854
01:10:31,876 --> 01:10:33,545
Mr. Kim,

855
01:10:33,546 --> 01:10:36,166
what about your family?

856
01:10:36,777 --> 01:10:40,607
Putting him in charge of the money is...

857
01:10:41,477 --> 01:10:44,515
This investment is for my family.

858
01:10:44,516 --> 01:10:46,086
Excuse me?

859
01:10:47,907 --> 01:10:49,986
I'm not sure

860
01:10:49,987 --> 01:10:52,265
how much longer

861
01:10:52,266 --> 01:10:54,067
my heart will last.

862
01:10:55,437 --> 01:10:59,415
Without me, what will happen to my mother,

863
01:10:59,416 --> 01:11:00,926
my wife, and kids?

864
01:11:02,697 --> 01:11:05,455
Anyone can talk my mother into signing

865
01:11:05,456 --> 01:11:08,015
any document they want, and my wife

866
01:11:08,016 --> 01:11:12,076
does not know how to deal with my mother.

867
01:11:12,077 --> 01:11:16,595
I need someone to be there for my family.

868
01:11:16,596 --> 01:11:19,965
Money aside, I know Taesu will

869
01:11:19,966 --> 01:11:22,766
take great care of my family.

870
01:11:23,987 --> 01:11:28,507
I know what kind of man he is.

871
01:11:37,147 --> 01:11:40,006
President Jang...

872
01:11:44,227 --> 01:11:46,396
You,

873
01:11:46,397 --> 01:11:48,165
you're lying, aren't you?

874
01:11:48,166 --> 01:11:49,406
How much money did Kim Jiwan give you?

875
01:11:49,407 --> 01:11:51,095
How much did it take to pay you off?

876
01:11:51,096 --> 01:11:52,607
President Jang...

877
01:12:07,206 --> 01:12:09,585
I need to see you right now.

878
01:12:09,586 --> 01:12:10,885
Come to my office.

879
01:12:10,886 --> 01:12:13,125
I'm not interested in seeing you.

880
01:12:13,126 --> 01:12:14,456
I'm hanging up.

881
01:12:20,867 --> 01:12:22,317
Take me to Kim Jiwan's apartment.

882
01:12:52,977 --> 01:12:54,885
I just

883
01:12:54,886 --> 01:12:58,296
met with Taehu Industry's company lawyer.

884
01:13:00,287 --> 01:13:02,066
Then you must've heard everything.

885
01:13:02,067 --> 01:13:03,497
Yes.

886
01:13:05,716 --> 01:13:10,346
You mean you heard about Sangjun?

887
01:13:11,266 --> 01:13:14,446
Your family's become quite crafty.

888
01:13:14,447 --> 01:13:16,217
Was it money, or something else?

889
01:13:16,218 --> 01:13:19,505
How did you make him lie to me like that?

890
01:13:19,506 --> 01:13:21,946
I remember him as a man of integrity,

891
01:13:21,947 --> 01:13:23,937
so how did you buy him off?

892
01:13:26,477 --> 01:13:30,326
You're well-prepared to taint my name.

893
01:13:30,327 --> 01:13:32,885
Turning Sangjun into a saint

894
01:13:32,886 --> 01:13:35,276
will make me look dirtier and pettier.

895
01:13:35,277 --> 01:13:36,715
On top of stealing money, I'd become

896
01:13:36,716 --> 01:13:40,765
a bastard who betrayed his best friend.

897
01:13:40,766 --> 01:13:42,805
Is that the plan?

898
01:13:42,806 --> 01:13:45,356
Telling the world how dirty and petty I am?

899
01:13:45,357 --> 01:13:47,747
That's what you're afraid of?

900
01:13:51,187 --> 01:13:53,375
I'm relieved.

901
01:13:53,376 --> 01:13:56,806
At least you know what you did was wrong.

902
01:14:01,237 --> 01:14:03,426
Why did you do it?

903
01:14:05,466 --> 01:14:08,176
You're not that type of person.

904
01:14:08,987 --> 01:14:11,415
You valued people,

905
01:14:11,416 --> 01:14:13,986
and you were very understanding.

906
01:14:15,527 --> 01:14:19,036
So Sangjun, Mother, and I

907
01:14:19,037 --> 01:14:22,345
trusted you with everything.

908
01:14:22,346 --> 01:14:25,056
You were upright and kindhearted.

909
01:14:28,447 --> 01:14:30,527
What happened to you?

910
01:14:32,626 --> 01:14:37,036
How did you end up here like this,

911
01:14:37,037 --> 01:14:41,667
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

912
01:14:51,857 --> 01:14:54,545
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

913
01:14:54,546 --> 01:14:56,026
bought that lawyer off.

914
01:14:56,027 --> 01:14:57,186
Taesu, what if...

915
01:14:57,187 --> 01:14:58,755
What if, what?

916
01:14:58,756 --> 01:15:00,616
You think it might be true?

917
01:15:00,617 --> 01:15:02,537
But if it's true, I'm...

918
01:15:07,676 --> 01:15:09,255
No.

919
01:15:09,256 --> 01:15:12,415
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

920
01:15:12,416 --> 01:15:15,595
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

921
01:15:15,596 --> 01:15:16,407
Wait...

922
01:15:16,408 --> 01:15:17,946
Wait, this means

923
01:15:17,947 --> 01:15:21,016
he can buy my people off, too.

924
01:15:22,437 --> 01:15:25,166
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

925
01:15:26,176 --> 01:15:27,466
Yes, sir.

926
01:15:37,176 --> 01:15:39,876
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

927
01:15:40,756 --> 01:15:41,816
I'm Kim Jiwan.

928
01:15:41,817 --> 01:15:43,117
Have a seat.

929
01:15:47,937 --> 01:15:51,425
I heard the news from a former employee.

930
01:15:51,426 --> 01:15:53,805
You've been contacting former directors?

931
01:15:53,806 --> 01:15:55,265
How many people have you met with?

932
01:15:55,266 --> 01:15:56,876
About twenty.

933
01:15:57,747 --> 01:15:59,526
And I've been preparing

934
01:15:59,527 --> 01:16:01,486
the recordings of their accounts.

935
01:16:01,487 --> 01:16:02,845
I think I can report the story right away

936
01:16:02,846 --> 01:16:05,606
if I had a copy of those recordings.

937
01:16:05,607 --> 01:16:07,955
Can you give me a copy?

938
01:16:07,956 --> 01:16:09,215
Of course.

939
01:16:09,216 --> 01:16:11,556
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

940
01:17:13,766 --> 01:17:16,367
Can't fall asleep?

941
01:17:18,886 --> 01:17:21,386
I can't seem to understand Father.

942
01:17:22,886 --> 01:17:26,345
Why did he try to put someone like

943
01:17:26,346 --> 01:17:28,987
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

944
01:17:30,817 --> 01:17:32,026
That was so foolish.

945
01:17:32,027 --> 01:17:33,407
Jiwan.

946
01:17:35,546 --> 01:17:38,187
Don't blame your father.

947
01:17:38,747 --> 01:17:42,215
Back then, the only person he could trust

948
01:17:42,216 --> 01:17:44,756
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

949
01:17:45,907 --> 01:17:49,186
With his health deteriorating,

950
01:17:49,187 --> 01:17:52,777
your father was afraid of the future.

951
01:17:53,437 --> 01:17:56,165
And he thought

952
01:17:56,166 --> 01:18:00,736
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

953
01:18:00,737 --> 01:18:02,907
He was wrong.

954
01:18:03,697 --> 01:18:05,746
He trusted the man

955
01:18:05,747 --> 01:18:08,387
who stole all his money the day he died.

956
01:18:08,388 --> 01:18:11,246
If it were me,

957
01:18:11,247 --> 01:18:12,997
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

958
01:18:14,376 --> 01:18:17,265
He was a different man

959
01:18:17,266 --> 01:18:19,476
from who he is now.

960
01:18:19,477 --> 01:18:21,526
And that's why I can't forgive him.

961
01:18:21,527 --> 01:18:23,606
As a human being,

962
01:18:23,607 --> 01:18:24,746
you cannot betray someone

963
01:18:24,747 --> 01:18:26,567
who trusts you.

964
01:20:11,426 --> 01:20:13,197
Hyeondo.

965
01:20:15,437 --> 01:20:19,857
Why not resign from your father's company?

966
01:20:23,827 --> 01:20:28,207
I'll look into another job for you.

967
01:20:31,937 --> 01:20:33,817
I should go to work.

968
01:20:44,706 --> 01:20:46,955
Sugyeong came to see you?

969
01:20:46,956 --> 01:20:50,376
She really begged for your forgiveness?

970
01:20:51,487 --> 01:20:54,817
Sugyeong looked really bad.

971
01:20:55,926 --> 01:20:58,186
I think she's miserable.

972
01:20:58,187 --> 01:20:59,736
She should be.

973
01:20:59,737 --> 01:21:01,186
Of course.

974
01:21:01,187 --> 01:21:04,296
If she's not, she's not human.

975
01:21:04,987 --> 01:21:08,616
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

976
01:21:08,617 --> 01:21:10,187
What?

977
01:21:10,937 --> 01:21:14,316
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

978
01:21:14,317 --> 01:21:16,665
Oh, my.

979
01:21:16,666 --> 01:21:18,916
You sure are a saint.

980
01:21:19,567 --> 01:21:21,417
She's going through a rough time after

981
01:21:21,418 --> 01:21:24,675
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

982
01:21:24,676 --> 01:21:27,937
You're the one I feel sorry for.

983
01:21:28,987 --> 01:21:34,515
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

984
01:21:34,516 --> 01:21:36,316
He's at the hospital.

985
01:21:36,317 --> 01:21:38,335
Hyeondo?

986
01:21:38,336 --> 01:21:39,955
How could a child be healthy

987
01:21:39,956 --> 01:21:42,286
when his parents have no morals?

988
01:21:42,287 --> 01:21:46,057
Karma passes down to children.

989
01:21:48,846 --> 01:21:52,556
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

990
01:21:53,176 --> 01:21:54,686
How could I say no to you?

991
01:21:54,687 --> 01:21:56,996
I had to do it.

992
01:21:56,997 --> 01:21:58,385
So I was thinking,

993
01:21:58,386 --> 01:22:00,316
I heard you might end up

994
01:22:00,317 --> 01:22:03,125
taking over the company.

995
01:22:03,126 --> 01:22:05,396
There's an idea

996
01:22:05,397 --> 01:22:08,915
I've been developing for five years,

997
01:22:08,916 --> 01:22:11,736
and going to Russia gave me

998
01:22:11,737 --> 01:22:13,805
reaffirmation on my idea.

999
01:22:13,806 --> 01:22:16,226
So I was wondering

1000
01:22:16,227 --> 01:22:19,476
if you could give me a chance

1001
01:22:19,477 --> 01:22:21,926
to present that idea to you.

1002
01:22:25,806 --> 01:22:27,506
Please don't joke around with me.

1003
01:22:28,197 --> 01:22:29,656
I'm not...

1004
01:22:29,657 --> 01:22:33,335
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

1005
01:22:33,336 --> 01:22:35,415
and made your life difficult.

1006
01:22:35,416 --> 01:22:39,356
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

1007
01:22:39,357 --> 01:22:41,385
yes, like in Chinese novels,

1008
01:22:41,386 --> 01:22:42,936
in order to make someone a hero,

1009
01:22:42,937 --> 01:22:45,015
people around him

1010
01:22:45,016 --> 01:22:47,805
create hardships for him.

1011
01:22:47,806 --> 01:22:49,755
All Chinese heroes are like that.

1012
01:22:49,756 --> 01:22:51,885
They prevail over and over again,

1013
01:22:51,886 --> 01:22:52,876
and accomplish...

1014
01:22:52,877 --> 01:22:54,476
It's okay.

1015
01:22:54,477 --> 01:22:55,407
No, I...

1016
01:22:55,408 --> 01:22:57,447
I said it's okay!

1017
01:22:58,117 --> 01:22:59,427
Why do you keep bugging me!

1018
01:22:59,428 --> 01:23:00,925
I said it's okay!

1019
01:23:00,926 --> 01:23:02,466
Something great.

1020
01:23:04,817 --> 01:23:06,146
I think you're mistaken.

1021
01:23:06,147 --> 01:23:07,606
It's okay.

1022
01:23:07,607 --> 01:23:09,966
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

1023
01:23:10,537 --> 01:23:11,927
No, I'm not mistaken.

1024
01:23:11,928 --> 01:23:13,885
I think you're mistaken.

1025
01:23:13,886 --> 01:23:16,756
It's not like that. Just think about it.

1026
01:23:17,237 --> 01:23:20,066
When you asked me for a favor like that,

1027
01:23:20,067 --> 01:23:23,837
wasn't it because we are close?

1028
01:23:24,876 --> 01:23:26,505
- Yes. / - Right?

1029
01:23:26,506 --> 01:23:32,066
So since we share a special relationship,

1030
01:23:32,067 --> 01:23:33,037
let me present it in a special...

1031
01:23:33,038 --> 01:23:34,147
Jiwan.

1032
01:23:34,556 --> 01:23:35,625
Hi, Eunsu.

1033
01:23:35,626 --> 01:23:36,955
Ms. Han Eunsu!

1034
01:23:36,956 --> 01:23:39,055
Oh? Hello.

1035
01:23:39,056 --> 01:23:40,546
What are you doing here?

1036
01:23:42,777 --> 01:23:44,346
Huh?

1037
01:23:46,416 --> 01:23:48,437
She's my little sister.

1038
01:23:49,437 --> 01:23:50,955
Your real sister?

1039
01:23:50,956 --> 01:23:52,076
Yes.

1040
01:23:52,397 --> 01:23:57,027
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

1041
01:23:58,666 --> 01:24:00,215
Jiwan, Eunsu.

1042
01:24:00,216 --> 01:24:02,107
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

1043
01:24:02,697 --> 01:24:03,705
Remember?

1044
01:24:03,706 --> 01:24:06,396
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

1045
01:24:06,397 --> 01:24:07,786
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

1046
01:24:07,787 --> 01:24:08,747
Oh, Aunt.

1047
01:24:08,748 --> 01:24:12,287
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

1048
01:24:13,806 --> 01:24:14,856
Hi.

1049
01:24:14,857 --> 01:24:18,106
I'm Park Haengsuk.

1050
01:24:18,107 --> 01:24:19,326
Excuse me?

1051
01:24:19,327 --> 01:24:21,165
Park...

1052
01:24:21,166 --> 01:24:24,946
You're his aunt, but
your last name is Park?

1053
01:24:26,676 --> 01:24:31,996
Kim, Han and Park.

1054
01:24:31,997 --> 01:24:34,617
A family with different last names?

1055
01:24:39,956 --> 01:24:42,585
What happened?

1056
01:24:42,586 --> 01:24:44,165
Why is that office empty?

1057
01:24:44,166 --> 01:24:46,885
All the desks and chairs are gone.

1058
01:24:46,886 --> 01:24:48,486
Oh, that office?

1059
01:24:48,487 --> 01:24:49,986
They moved out.

1060
01:24:49,987 --> 01:24:51,736
They moved out?

1061
01:24:51,737 --> 01:24:53,915
Where did they go?

1062
01:24:53,916 --> 01:24:55,635
Where are my daughter and husband?

1063
01:24:55,636 --> 01:25:00,636
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

1064
01:25:03,437 --> 01:25:04,987
A, a tent?

1065
01:25:11,846 --> 01:25:12,965
Oh,

1066
01:25:12,966 --> 01:25:16,455
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

1067
01:25:16,456 --> 01:25:17,736
When is the phone guy coming?

1068
01:25:17,737 --> 01:25:19,595
He'll be here at 3.

1069
01:25:19,596 --> 01:25:21,585
Where should the line go?

1070
01:25:21,586 --> 01:25:23,096
I'll find a spot.

1071
01:25:23,477 --> 01:25:24,787
I'll take that, Yeongju.

1072
01:25:31,876 --> 01:25:33,925
You shouldn't bite off
more than you can chew,

1073
01:25:33,926 --> 01:25:35,555
and mingle with your own kind!

1074
01:25:35,556 --> 01:25:38,755
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

1075
01:25:38,756 --> 01:25:40,656
It's my fault for signing a contract

1076
01:25:40,657 --> 01:25:43,226
that says the owner can
evict us at any time.

1077
01:25:43,227 --> 01:25:44,936
How dare you side with Jiwan!

1078
01:25:44,937 --> 01:25:46,907
I'm going to get him for this!

1079
01:25:48,037 --> 01:25:49,147
Honey, Mi...

1080
01:25:52,506 --> 01:25:54,056
What did Mom say?

1081
01:25:55,796 --> 01:25:58,696
She's going to get Jiwan.

1082
01:25:58,697 --> 01:26:00,007
What?

1083
01:26:00,787 --> 01:26:01,727
Seriously...

1084
01:26:01,728 --> 01:26:03,056
Let's hurry up.

1085
01:26:07,016 --> 01:26:08,506
Jiwan, you!

1086
01:26:08,747 --> 01:26:09,617
Hello.

1087
01:26:09,618 --> 01:26:10,917
Just a second.

1088
01:26:11,357 --> 01:26:12,627
Hello.

1089
01:26:13,407 --> 01:26:16,167
It's an important meeting. This way.

1090
01:26:16,617 --> 01:26:18,686
Everything looks great.

1091
01:26:18,687 --> 01:26:22,385
I can see, now that I'm here.

1092
01:26:22,386 --> 01:26:26,015
You put up a makeshift
office near the farm.

1093
01:26:26,016 --> 01:26:29,896
It shows your concern for quality control.

1094
01:26:29,897 --> 01:26:31,186
I just need to sign here, yes?

1095
01:26:31,187 --> 01:26:32,586
Yes.

1096
01:26:38,067 --> 01:26:39,236
Thank you.

1097
01:26:39,237 --> 01:26:40,207
I hope this works out great.

1098
01:26:40,208 --> 01:26:41,236
Thank you.

1099
01:26:46,897 --> 01:26:47,955
Goodbye.

1100
01:26:47,956 --> 01:26:50,236
That guy

1101
01:26:50,237 --> 01:26:51,936
is great at many things.

1102
01:26:51,937 --> 01:26:53,786
He's amazing.

1103
01:26:53,787 --> 01:26:56,207
He performs better under pressure.

1104
01:26:57,586 --> 01:27:00,095
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

1105
01:27:00,096 --> 01:27:01,526
And it's such a hot day.

1106
01:27:01,527 --> 01:27:04,106
Let me get you something cool to drink.

1107
01:27:04,107 --> 01:27:05,426
Mr. Jang.

1108
01:27:11,516 --> 01:27:13,527
This is worth $30,000.

1109
01:27:18,056 --> 01:27:21,425
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

1110
01:27:21,426 --> 01:27:23,215
Hey, cut me some slack.

1111
01:27:23,216 --> 01:27:24,625
I was caught off guard.

1112
01:27:24,626 --> 01:27:25,955
It slipped out.

1113
01:27:25,956 --> 01:27:27,246
I can't believe you.

1114
01:27:27,546 --> 01:27:30,397
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

1115
01:27:31,676 --> 01:27:32,795
Director, you're here.

1116
01:27:32,796 --> 01:27:34,205
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

1117
01:27:34,206 --> 01:27:35,566
Yes.

1118
01:27:36,766 --> 01:27:38,056
What are you doing here?

1119
01:27:38,607 --> 01:27:40,005
What do you think?

1120
01:27:40,006 --> 01:27:41,826
They are working so hard on a hot day,

1121
01:27:41,827 --> 01:27:43,347
so I bought them Korean pork

1122
01:27:43,348 --> 01:27:45,946
to help them restore some energy.

1123
01:27:45,947 --> 01:27:48,826
Domestic is always the best.

1124
01:27:48,827 --> 01:27:51,217
Of course. You're a wise man.

1125
01:27:52,756 --> 01:27:55,415
Honey, don't just stand there.
Come and sit.

1126
01:27:55,416 --> 01:27:57,026
- Come here. / - Yeongju,
come and sit down.

1127
01:27:57,027 --> 01:27:58,496
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

1128
01:27:58,497 --> 01:27:59,597
Let me go get some more lettuce.

1129
01:27:59,598 --> 01:28:00,806
Okay.

1130
01:28:07,027 --> 01:28:08,236
Wait,

1131
01:28:08,237 --> 01:28:10,396
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

1132
01:28:10,397 --> 01:28:11,746
What's going on?

1133
01:28:11,747 --> 01:28:13,026
Oh, I can't believe you.

1134
01:28:13,027 --> 01:28:15,087
When? People might actually believe that.

1135
01:28:15,088 --> 01:28:17,186
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

1136
01:28:17,187 --> 01:28:20,656
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

1137
01:28:20,657 --> 01:28:23,446
so I bought him Korean pork,

1138
01:28:23,447 --> 01:28:25,385
to help him restore energy.

1139
01:28:25,386 --> 01:28:27,845
Why are you just sitting there?

1140
01:28:27,846 --> 01:28:29,625
Go and help wash the lettuce.

1141
01:28:29,626 --> 01:28:30,816
Go help Jiwan.

1142
01:28:31,266 --> 01:28:32,737
Okay.

1143
01:28:34,386 --> 01:28:38,165
I'm a great judge of character.

1144
01:28:38,166 --> 01:28:41,976
Mom, just have one spoonful.

1145
01:28:41,977 --> 01:28:42,846
Say ah.

1146
01:28:42,847 --> 01:28:45,826
I don't want any chicken porridge.

1147
01:28:45,827 --> 01:28:48,755
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

1148
01:28:48,756 --> 01:28:51,255
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

1149
01:28:51,256 --> 01:28:53,925
so you can restore energy, okay?

1150
01:28:53,926 --> 01:28:56,146
Just have one spoonful.

1151
01:28:56,147 --> 01:28:57,277
Say ah.

1152
01:29:03,206 --> 01:29:05,125
See?

1153
01:29:05,126 --> 01:29:08,015
You're upset because of what you said.

1154
01:29:08,016 --> 01:29:10,436
I didn't say anything wrong.

1155
01:29:10,437 --> 01:29:13,795
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

1156
01:29:13,796 --> 01:29:16,736
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

1157
01:29:18,447 --> 01:29:20,116
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

1158
01:29:20,117 --> 01:29:22,567
and meets someone nice.

1159
01:29:23,527 --> 01:29:25,846
I'm sure she will.

1160
01:29:26,437 --> 01:29:29,107
Couples form and break up all the time.

1161
01:29:31,237 --> 01:29:34,305
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

1162
01:29:34,306 --> 01:29:37,556
Jiwan has no time for that.

1163
01:29:39,697 --> 01:29:40,907
This?

1164
01:29:44,206 --> 01:29:45,706
You see,

1165
01:29:46,187 --> 01:29:49,817
here are the size and unit.

1166
01:29:53,077 --> 01:29:55,056
Hi.

1167
01:29:57,367 --> 01:30:00,577
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

1168
01:30:00,876 --> 01:30:03,026
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

1169
01:30:03,027 --> 01:30:04,707
But why are you here?

1170
01:30:07,147 --> 01:30:09,585
Oh, I'm stuffed.

1171
01:30:09,586 --> 01:30:13,465
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

1172
01:30:13,466 --> 01:30:14,946
You ate a lot of it.

1173
01:30:14,947 --> 01:30:16,447
Because it was delicious.

1174
01:30:19,407 --> 01:30:22,536
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

1175
01:30:22,537 --> 01:30:24,657
It's okay. I can go home alone.

1176
01:30:25,086 --> 01:30:26,006
Don't say that.

1177
01:30:26,007 --> 01:30:28,286
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

1178
01:30:28,287 --> 01:30:29,385
Take her home.

1179
01:30:29,386 --> 01:30:30,896
No, that's not going to happen.

1180
01:30:30,897 --> 01:30:32,457
Don't say that. Just go.

1181
01:30:32,458 --> 01:30:34,026
What are you two doing?

1182
01:30:34,027 --> 01:30:35,425
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

1183
01:30:35,426 --> 01:30:37,335
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

1184
01:30:37,336 --> 01:30:38,616
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

1185
01:30:38,617 --> 01:30:39,577
Okay.

1186
01:30:39,578 --> 01:30:40,937
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

1187
01:30:52,846 --> 01:30:54,977
Are those two dating?

1188
01:30:55,666 --> 01:30:57,786
They're not together yet,

1189
01:30:57,787 --> 01:31:00,707
but they are testing the waters.

1190
01:31:02,527 --> 01:31:05,205
It's frustrating to watch them.

1191
01:31:05,206 --> 01:31:06,836
Yeongju...

1192
01:31:07,567 --> 01:31:08,996
She's nice.

1193
01:31:08,997 --> 01:31:10,335
She is.

1194
01:31:10,336 --> 01:31:12,526
She's pretty and pleasant.

1195
01:31:12,527 --> 01:31:15,776
And she's a teacher.

1196
01:31:15,777 --> 01:31:16,925
Don't you think they look good together?

1197
01:31:16,926 --> 01:31:18,616
Yes, they do.

1198
01:31:29,067 --> 01:31:30,287
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

1199
01:31:54,636 --> 01:31:57,165
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

1200
01:31:57,166 --> 01:31:59,026
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

1201
01:32:00,716 --> 01:32:02,296
I'm just practicing.

1202
01:32:02,706 --> 01:32:04,246
Practicing?

1203
01:32:07,897 --> 01:32:10,066
Oh, I get it.

1204
01:32:10,067 --> 01:32:11,095
Girl...

1205
01:32:11,096 --> 01:32:14,486
You have a good eye.

1206
01:32:14,487 --> 01:32:15,297
What do you mean?

1207
01:32:15,298 --> 01:32:17,175
Jiwan.

1208
01:32:17,176 --> 01:32:18,856
Who cares about education?

1209
01:32:18,857 --> 01:32:22,356
To me, money trumps everything.

1210
01:32:22,357 --> 01:32:25,357
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

1211
01:32:27,876 --> 01:32:29,715
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

1212
01:32:29,716 --> 01:32:31,996
Eunsu is easy.

1213
01:32:31,997 --> 01:32:35,427
The grandmother-in-law
will become forgetful.

1214
01:32:36,037 --> 01:32:39,976
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

1215
01:32:39,977 --> 01:32:41,866
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

1216
01:32:41,867 --> 01:32:43,226
I told you it's not like that.

1217
01:32:43,227 --> 01:32:44,096
Just leave me alone.

1218
01:32:44,097 --> 01:32:46,986
How could I leave you alone?

1219
01:32:46,987 --> 01:32:48,635
You won't go on blind dates,

1220
01:32:48,636 --> 01:32:50,966
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

1221
01:32:52,016 --> 01:32:53,505
If it were me in the old days,

1222
01:32:53,506 --> 01:32:55,426
I would've already...

1223
01:32:56,176 --> 01:32:57,896
What's the use of giving you my looks?

1224
01:32:57,897 --> 01:32:59,545
Just look at yourself.

1225
01:32:59,546 --> 01:33:02,625
You're dressed like a tomboy,

1226
01:33:02,626 --> 01:33:04,505
and you haven't taken a shower.

1227
01:33:04,506 --> 01:33:07,455
You need to make yourself look pretty!

1228
01:33:07,456 --> 01:33:10,146
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

1229
01:33:10,147 --> 01:33:12,646
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

1230
01:33:12,647 --> 01:33:14,116
You have to look pretty!

1231
01:33:14,117 --> 01:33:15,976
What good will cooking do for you?

1232
01:33:15,977 --> 01:33:17,345
Besides your pretty face,

1233
01:33:17,346 --> 01:33:20,095
you got nothing from me!

1234
01:33:20,096 --> 01:33:22,407
What do you mean? Like this?

1235
01:33:25,367 --> 01:33:26,536
Oh, you're impossible.

1236
01:33:26,537 --> 01:33:28,986
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

1237
01:33:28,987 --> 01:33:31,857
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

1238
01:33:34,437 --> 01:33:35,505
Minja.

1239
01:33:35,506 --> 01:33:36,426
Oh!

1240
01:33:36,426 --> 01:33:37,397
Ms. Lee!

1241
01:33:37,398 --> 01:33:38,446
What are you doing here?

1242
01:33:38,447 --> 01:33:41,746
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

1243
01:33:41,747 --> 01:33:43,237
What about you?

1244
01:33:43,876 --> 01:33:46,727
Yeongju's been complaining
about neck pain, too.

1245
01:33:48,016 --> 01:33:49,295
Well,

1246
01:33:49,296 --> 01:33:52,906
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

1247
01:33:54,386 --> 01:33:55,715
I've given up on that.

1248
01:33:55,716 --> 01:33:57,066
How they feel about each
other is important,

1249
01:33:57,067 --> 01:33:58,796
not their background.

1250
01:33:59,247 --> 01:34:02,055
You're right!

1251
01:34:02,056 --> 01:34:07,237
But I heard you hold education very high.

1252
01:34:08,117 --> 01:34:11,406
If they're in love,
education doesn't matter.

1253
01:34:11,407 --> 01:34:14,447
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

1254
01:34:15,187 --> 01:34:20,306
But isn't a small family better?

1255
01:34:21,136 --> 01:34:24,476
I would prefer a small family,

1256
01:34:24,477 --> 01:34:25,875
but these days, as complicated as it is,

1257
01:34:25,876 --> 01:34:29,165
people don't live with married children.

1258
01:34:29,166 --> 01:34:31,586
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

1259
01:34:32,727 --> 01:34:34,286
But that's...

1260
01:34:34,287 --> 01:34:36,125
Well...

1261
01:34:36,126 --> 01:34:38,496
Old people don't live forever.

1262
01:34:38,497 --> 01:34:41,197
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

1263
01:34:41,727 --> 01:34:44,246
I'm not going to let my daughter

1264
01:34:44,247 --> 01:34:46,057
date anyone with a large family.

1265
01:34:46,058 --> 01:34:48,465
What if she gets stuck with them?

1266
01:34:48,466 --> 01:34:50,286
That won't be good.

1267
01:34:51,916 --> 01:34:55,096
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

1268
01:34:55,437 --> 01:34:57,207
As long as they live separately,

1269
01:34:57,208 --> 01:34:59,776
you don't mind a big family?

1270
01:34:59,777 --> 01:35:01,326
Of course not.

1271
01:35:01,327 --> 01:35:03,627
As long as they are in love.

1272
01:35:04,506 --> 01:35:05,397
Why do you ask?

1273
01:35:05,398 --> 01:35:09,186
You have someone in mind?

1274
01:35:09,187 --> 01:35:10,636
Of course.

1275
01:35:12,456 --> 01:35:14,616
- You do? / - Yes.

1276
01:35:25,787 --> 01:35:28,555
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

1277
01:35:28,556 --> 01:35:32,316
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

1278
01:35:32,317 --> 01:35:35,356
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

1279
01:35:35,357 --> 01:35:38,566
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

1280
01:35:38,567 --> 01:35:40,146
There are protocols for reporters...

1281
01:35:40,147 --> 01:35:41,736
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

1282
01:35:41,737 --> 01:35:44,457
former directors will be giving statements!

1283
01:35:44,458 --> 01:35:45,845
Tell me if it's true,

1284
01:35:45,846 --> 01:35:48,095
or if it's slander!

1285
01:35:48,096 --> 01:35:51,005
President Jang!

1286
01:35:51,006 --> 01:35:52,126
Please leave.

1287
01:35:55,437 --> 01:35:57,466
Refuse all interviews.

1288
01:35:58,086 --> 01:35:59,626
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

1289
01:36:00,516 --> 01:36:02,955
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

1290
01:36:02,956 --> 01:36:04,996
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

1291
01:36:06,867 --> 01:36:08,095
If he had all the evidence,

1292
01:36:08,096 --> 01:36:10,216
he would've written about it already.

1293
01:36:10,977 --> 01:36:13,465
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

1294
01:36:13,466 --> 01:36:16,816
I told you to find him, by any means!

1295
01:36:16,817 --> 01:36:17,657
What are you doing?

1296
01:36:17,658 --> 01:36:19,487
Is it that you can't or won't?

1297
01:36:21,846 --> 01:36:23,566
Seokjin was

1298
01:36:23,567 --> 01:36:26,305
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

1299
01:36:26,306 --> 01:36:28,306
and is still with us today.

1300
01:36:29,386 --> 01:36:32,595
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

1301
01:36:32,596 --> 01:36:35,006
whenever we reach a new milestone.

1302
01:36:36,397 --> 01:36:40,255
Hyeokju practically lived with us

1303
01:36:40,256 --> 01:36:41,937
at the factory.

1304
01:36:43,056 --> 01:36:45,515
So how could I

1305
01:36:45,516 --> 01:36:48,926
dig into their past, and make threats?

1306
01:36:49,907 --> 01:36:51,437
Taesu!

1307
01:36:54,867 --> 01:36:57,397
You've been paid off, too?

1308
01:36:59,857 --> 01:37:02,946
I know you met with Seokjin.

1309
01:37:02,947 --> 01:37:05,127
I wasn't sure.

1310
01:37:05,617 --> 01:37:06,936
So, what did you get from them?

1311
01:37:06,937 --> 01:37:09,867
How much did they pay you!

1312
01:37:10,497 --> 01:37:11,885
Taesu...

1313
01:37:11,886 --> 01:37:13,135
Get out.

1314
01:37:13,136 --> 01:37:14,116
You're fired!

1315
01:37:14,117 --> 01:37:15,487
Get lost!

1316
01:38:17,636 --> 01:38:19,286
Hyeondo,

1317
01:38:20,016 --> 01:38:22,746
I once told your father

1318
01:38:22,747 --> 01:38:25,037
to watch his back because of you.

1319
01:38:27,647 --> 01:38:30,027
And he said to me,

1320
01:38:31,687 --> 01:38:33,747
even if you betrayed him, that was okay.

1321
01:38:34,947 --> 01:38:36,926
Because you're his son.

1322
01:38:41,037 --> 01:38:43,057
Look after Taesu.

1323
01:38:45,277 --> 01:38:47,777
I can't seem to do it anymore.

1324
01:39:41,666 --> 01:39:45,015
Is this Mr. Han Yeongho of Daehan Daily?

1325
01:39:45,016 --> 01:39:46,886
This is Kim Jiwan.

1326
01:39:48,117 --> 01:39:51,507
Can we have that interview tomorrow?

1327
01:39:58,577 --> 01:40:00,197
Yes, Mr. Han.

1328
01:40:01,456 --> 01:40:03,136
I'm on my way.

1329
01:41:01,817 --> 01:41:03,377
Your father was going to

1330
01:41:04,586 --> 01:41:08,176
hand over his company to my father?

1331
01:41:11,456 --> 01:41:13,956
I couldn't understand him at first,

1332
01:41:16,237 --> 01:41:19,236
but now that I think about it,

1333
01:41:19,237 --> 01:41:21,167
I can understand him a little bit.

1334
01:41:34,716 --> 01:41:36,836
This is all the evidence I've collected.

1335
01:41:41,197 --> 01:41:43,087
Why are you giving them to me?

1336
01:41:48,227 --> 01:41:50,246
Why did you

1337
01:41:50,247 --> 01:41:52,407
give me that notebook?

1338
01:42:25,806 --> 01:42:27,126
Have you had a lot to drink?

1339
01:42:28,456 --> 01:42:31,977
You asked me here, so why are you late?

1340
01:42:36,596 --> 01:42:38,527
I met Jiwan.

1341
01:42:41,956 --> 01:42:44,236
Uncle Sangjun

1342
01:42:45,916 --> 01:42:49,227
was going to give you all his money?

1343
01:42:49,977 --> 01:42:51,886
That's a lie.

1344
01:42:52,657 --> 01:42:54,577
Right?

1345
01:42:58,037 --> 01:43:00,896
Who would actually do that?

1346
01:43:00,897 --> 01:43:03,226
Why would he give you his company

1347
01:43:03,227 --> 01:43:05,845
when he has a son and a family?

1348
01:43:05,846 --> 01:43:07,766
That's ridiculous.

1349
01:43:08,426 --> 01:43:10,246
You were just a friend.

1350
01:43:11,367 --> 01:43:13,157
Not his blood.

1351
01:43:17,187 --> 01:43:19,096
Don't you agree?

1352
01:43:20,737 --> 01:43:22,317
Yes.

1353
01:43:22,916 --> 01:43:24,896
I'm not his blood.

1354
01:43:27,787 --> 01:43:30,097
But,

1355
01:43:30,926 --> 01:43:33,675
even though I wasn't his blood,

1356
01:43:33,676 --> 01:43:37,316
Sangjun might have actually really

1357
01:43:37,317 --> 01:43:41,466
wanted to give me his company.

1358
01:43:44,456 --> 01:43:48,026
But why...

1359
01:43:48,027 --> 01:43:50,547
How could he trust me so much?

1360
01:44:28,016 --> 01:44:29,256
Jiwan.

1361
01:44:32,657 --> 01:44:35,996
Do you

1362
01:44:35,997 --> 01:44:38,877
remember Dad?

1363
01:44:41,907 --> 01:44:43,766
A little bit.

1364
01:44:46,876 --> 01:44:52,616
What kind of person was he?

1365
01:44:55,497 --> 01:44:58,687
He smiled at me whenever he saw me.

1366
01:45:06,237 --> 01:45:08,797
Why did

1367
01:45:10,666 --> 01:45:14,977
Dad trust a man like him?

1368
01:45:17,166 --> 01:45:19,766
He was so foolish.

1369
01:45:24,237 --> 01:45:27,216
You think so, too, don't you?

1370
01:46:37,916 --> 01:46:39,336
How have you been?

1371
01:46:52,216 --> 01:46:54,286
Don't turn bad.

1372
01:46:56,756 --> 01:46:59,426
That's not who you are, Hyeondo.

1373
01:47:10,357 --> 01:47:11,966
I should go.

1374
01:47:51,977 --> 01:47:53,215
The Korean Businessmen's Association

1375
01:47:53,216 --> 01:47:57,036
recommended you as a next chairperson.

1376
01:47:57,497 --> 01:48:01,427
You're to give an acceptance speech.

1377
01:48:02,876 --> 01:48:04,116
Okay.

1378
01:48:04,117 --> 01:48:05,596
I got it.

1379
01:48:06,176 --> 01:48:07,625
Oh, and

1380
01:48:07,626 --> 01:48:09,726
call my wife's lawyer,

1381
01:48:09,727 --> 01:48:11,746
and have him visit me here.

1382
01:48:11,747 --> 01:48:13,187
Yes, sir.

1383
01:48:21,277 --> 01:48:23,226
President Jang wants to see you

1384
01:48:23,227 --> 01:48:25,107
before going to court.

1385
01:48:26,407 --> 01:48:28,036
What is it about?

1386
