1656
02:15:19,747 --> 02:15:24,377
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

1657
02:15:34,567 --> 02:15:37,255
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

1658
02:15:37,256 --> 02:15:38,736
bought that lawyer off.

1659
02:15:38,737 --> 02:15:39,896
Taesu, what if...

1660
02:15:39,897 --> 02:15:41,465
What if, what?

1661
02:15:41,466 --> 02:15:43,326
You think it might be true?

1662
02:15:43,327 --> 02:15:45,247
But if it's true, I'm...

1663
02:15:50,386 --> 02:15:51,965
No.

1664
02:15:51,966 --> 02:15:55,125
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

1665
02:15:55,126 --> 02:15:58,305
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

1666
02:15:58,306 --> 02:15:59,117
Wait...

1667
02:15:59,118 --> 02:16:00,656
Wait, this means

1668
02:16:00,657 --> 02:16:03,727
he can buy my people off, too.

1669
02:16:05,147 --> 02:16:07,876
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

1670
02:16:08,886 --> 02:16:10,176
Yes, sir.

1671
02:16:19,886 --> 02:16:22,586
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

1672
02:16:23,466 --> 02:16:24,526
I'm Kim Jiwan.

1673
02:16:24,527 --> 02:16:25,827
Have a seat.

1674
02:16:30,647 --> 02:16:34,135
I heard the news from a former employee.

1675
02:16:34,136 --> 02:16:36,516
You've been contacting former directors?

1676
02:16:36,517 --> 02:16:37,976
How many people have you met with?

1677
02:16:37,977 --> 02:16:39,587
About twenty.

1678
02:16:40,456 --> 02:16:42,236
And I've been preparing

1679
02:16:42,237 --> 02:16:44,195
the recordings of their accounts.

1680
02:16:44,196 --> 02:16:45,555
I think I can report the story right away

1681
02:16:45,556 --> 02:16:48,316
if I had a copy of those recordings.

1682
02:16:48,317 --> 02:16:50,666
Can you give me a copy?

1683
02:16:50,667 --> 02:16:51,926
Of course.

1684
02:16:51,927 --> 02:16:54,267
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

1685
02:17:56,477 --> 02:17:59,077
Can't fall asleep?

1686
02:18:01,597 --> 02:18:04,097
I can't seem to understand Father.

1687
02:18:05,597 --> 02:18:09,055
Why did he try to put someone like

1688
02:18:09,056 --> 02:18:11,696
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

1689
02:18:13,526 --> 02:18:14,736
That was so foolish.

1690
02:18:14,737 --> 02:18:16,116
Jiwan.

1691
02:18:18,257 --> 02:18:20,897
Don't blame your father.

1692
02:18:21,456 --> 02:18:24,926
Back then, the only person he could trust

1693
02:18:24,927 --> 02:18:27,467
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

1694
02:18:28,616 --> 02:18:31,896
With his health deteriorating,

1695
02:18:31,897 --> 02:18:35,487
your father was afraid of the future.

1696
02:18:36,147 --> 02:18:38,875
And he thought

1697
02:18:38,876 --> 02:18:43,445
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

1698
02:18:43,446 --> 02:18:45,616
He was wrong.

1699
02:18:46,407 --> 02:18:48,455
He trusted the man

1700
02:18:48,456 --> 02:18:51,096
who stole all his money the day he died.

1701
02:18:51,097 --> 02:18:53,955
If it were me,

1702
02:18:53,956 --> 02:18:55,706
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

1703
02:18:57,087 --> 02:18:59,976
He was a different man

1704
02:18:59,977 --> 02:19:02,185
from who he is now.

1705
02:19:02,186 --> 02:19:04,236
And that's why I can't forgive him.

1706
02:19:04,237 --> 02:19:06,316
As a human being,

1707
02:19:06,317 --> 02:19:07,455
you cannot betray someone

1708
02:19:07,456 --> 02:19:09,276
who trusts you.

1709
02:20:54,136 --> 02:20:55,907
Hyeondo.

1710
02:20:58,147 --> 02:21:02,567
Why not resign from your father's company?

1711
02:21:06,536 --> 02:21:10,916
I'll look into another job for you.

1712
02:21:14,647 --> 02:21:16,526
I should go to work.

1713
02:21:27,417 --> 02:21:29,666
Sugyeong came to see you?

1714
02:21:29,667 --> 02:21:33,087
She really begged for your forgiveness?

1715
02:21:34,196 --> 02:21:37,526
Sugyeong looked really bad.

1716
02:21:38,636 --> 02:21:40,896
I think she's miserable.

1717
02:21:40,897 --> 02:21:42,445
She should be.

1718
02:21:42,446 --> 02:21:43,896
Of course.

1719
02:21:43,897 --> 02:21:47,007
If she's not, she's not human.

1720
02:21:47,696 --> 02:21:51,326
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

1721
02:21:51,327 --> 02:21:52,897
What?

1722
02:21:53,647 --> 02:21:57,025
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

1723
02:21:57,026 --> 02:21:59,375
Oh, my.

1724
02:21:59,376 --> 02:22:01,626
You sure are a saint.

1725
02:22:02,276 --> 02:22:04,125
She's going through a rough time after

1726
02:22:04,126 --> 02:22:07,385
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

1727
02:22:07,386 --> 02:22:10,647
You're the one I feel sorry for.

1728
02:22:11,696 --> 02:22:17,226
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

1729
02:22:17,227 --> 02:22:19,025
He's at the hospital.

1730
02:22:19,026 --> 02:22:21,045
Hyeondo?

1731
02:22:21,046 --> 02:22:22,666
How could a child be healthy

1732
02:22:22,667 --> 02:22:24,996
when his parents have no morals?

1733
02:22:24,997 --> 02:22:28,767
Karma passes down to children.

1734
02:22:31,556 --> 02:22:35,266
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

1735
02:22:35,886 --> 02:22:37,396
How could I say no to you?

1736
02:22:37,397 --> 02:22:39,705
I had to do it.

1737
02:22:39,706 --> 02:22:41,096
So I was thinking,

1738
02:22:41,097 --> 02:22:43,025
I heard you might end up

1739
02:22:43,026 --> 02:22:45,836
taking over the company.

1740
02:22:45,837 --> 02:22:48,105
There's an idea

1741
02:22:48,106 --> 02:22:51,625
I've been developing for five years,

1742
02:22:51,626 --> 02:22:54,445
and going to Russia gave me

1743
02:22:54,446 --> 02:22:56,516
reaffirmation on my idea.

1744
02:22:56,517 --> 02:22:58,935
So I was wondering

1745
02:22:58,936 --> 02:23:02,185
if you could give me a chance

1746
02:23:02,186 --> 02:23:04,636
to present that idea to you.

1747
02:23:08,517 --> 02:23:10,217
Please don't joke around with me.

1748
02:23:10,907 --> 02:23:12,365
I'm not...

1749
02:23:12,366 --> 02:23:16,045
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

1750
02:23:16,046 --> 02:23:18,125
and made your life difficult.

1751
02:23:18,126 --> 02:23:22,066
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

1752
02:23:22,067 --> 02:23:24,096
yes, like in Chinese novels,

1753
02:23:24,097 --> 02:23:25,646
in order to make someone a hero,

1754
02:23:25,647 --> 02:23:27,726
people around him

1755
02:23:27,727 --> 02:23:30,516
create hardships for him.

1756
02:23:30,517 --> 02:23:32,467
All Chinese heroes are like that.

1757
02:23:32,468 --> 02:23:34,596
They prevail over and over again,

1758
02:23:34,597 --> 02:23:35,587
and accomplish...

1759
02:23:35,588 --> 02:23:37,185
It's okay.

1760
02:23:37,186 --> 02:23:38,116
No, I...

1761
02:23:38,117 --> 02:23:40,157
I said it's okay!

1762
02:23:40,827 --> 02:23:42,135
Why do you keep bugging me!

1763
02:23:42,136 --> 02:23:43,635
I said it's okay!

1764
02:23:43,636 --> 02:23:45,177
Something great.

1765
02:23:47,526 --> 02:23:48,855
I think you're mistaken.

1766
02:23:48,856 --> 02:23:50,316
It's okay.

1767
02:23:50,317 --> 02:23:52,677
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

1768
02:23:53,247 --> 02:23:54,635
No, I'm not mistaken.

1769
02:23:54,636 --> 02:23:56,596
I think you're mistaken.

1770
02:23:56,597 --> 02:23:59,467
It's not like that. Just think about it.

1771
02:23:59,946 --> 02:24:02,775
When you asked me for a favor like that,

1772
02:24:02,776 --> 02:24:06,546
wasn't it because we are close?

1773
02:24:07,587 --> 02:24:09,215
- Yes. / - Right?

1774
02:24:09,216 --> 02:24:14,775
So since we share a special relationship,

1775
02:24:14,776 --> 02:24:15,746
let me present it in a special...

1776
02:24:15,747 --> 02:24:16,857
Jiwan.

1777
02:24:17,267 --> 02:24:18,336
Hi, Eunsu.

1778
02:24:18,337 --> 02:24:19,666
Ms. Han Eunsu!

1779
02:24:19,667 --> 02:24:21,766
Oh? Hello.

1780
02:24:21,767 --> 02:24:23,257
What are you doing here?

1781
02:24:25,487 --> 02:24:27,056
Huh?

1782
02:24:29,126 --> 02:24:31,147
She's my little sister.

1783
02:24:32,147 --> 02:24:33,666
Your real sister?

1784
02:24:33,667 --> 02:24:34,787
Yes.

1785
02:24:35,106 --> 02:24:39,736
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

1786
02:24:41,376 --> 02:24:42,926
Jiwan, Eunsu.

1787
02:24:42,927 --> 02:24:44,817
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

1788
02:24:45,407 --> 02:24:46,416
Remember?

1789
02:24:46,417 --> 02:24:49,105
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

1790
02:24:49,106 --> 02:24:50,496
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

1791
02:24:50,497 --> 02:24:51,456
Oh, Aunt.

1792
02:24:51,457 --> 02:24:54,997
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

1793
02:24:56,517 --> 02:24:57,566
Hi.

1794
02:24:57,567 --> 02:25:00,816
I'm Park Haengsuk.

1795
02:25:00,817 --> 02:25:02,035
Excuse me?

1796
02:25:02,036 --> 02:25:03,875
Park...

1797
02:25:03,876 --> 02:25:07,657
You're his aunt, but
your last name is Park?

1798
02:25:09,386 --> 02:25:14,705
Kim, Han and Park.

1799
02:25:14,706 --> 02:25:17,327
A family with different last names?

1800
02:25:22,667 --> 02:25:25,295
What happened?

1801
02:25:25,296 --> 02:25:26,875
Why is that office empty?

1802
02:25:26,876 --> 02:25:29,596
All the desks and chairs are gone.

1803
02:25:29,597 --> 02:25:31,195
Oh, that office?

1804
02:25:31,196 --> 02:25:32,695
They moved out.

1805
02:25:32,696 --> 02:25:34,445
They moved out?

1806
02:25:34,446 --> 02:25:36,625
Where did they go?

1807
02:25:36,626 --> 02:25:38,346
Where are my daughter and husband?

1808
02:25:38,347 --> 02:25:43,347
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

1809
02:25:46,147 --> 02:25:47,696
A, a tent?

1810
02:25:54,556 --> 02:25:55,676
Oh,

1811
02:25:55,677 --> 02:25:59,166
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

1812
02:25:59,167 --> 02:26:00,447
When is the phone guy coming?

1813
02:26:00,448 --> 02:26:02,305
He'll be here at 3.

1814
02:26:02,306 --> 02:26:04,295
Where should the line go?

1815
02:26:04,296 --> 02:26:05,806
I'll find a spot.

1816
02:26:06,186 --> 02:26:07,496
I'll take that, Yeongju.

1817
02:26:14,587 --> 02:26:16,635
You shouldn't bite off
more than you can chew,

1818
02:26:16,636 --> 02:26:18,266
and mingle with your own kind!

1819
02:26:18,267 --> 02:26:21,465
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

1820
02:26:21,466 --> 02:26:23,365
It's my fault for signing a contract

1821
02:26:23,366 --> 02:26:25,935
that says the owner can
evict us at any time.

1822
02:26:25,936 --> 02:26:27,646
How dare you side with Jiwan!

1823
02:26:27,647 --> 02:26:29,616
I'm going to get him for this!

1824
02:26:30,747 --> 02:26:31,857
Honey, Mi...

1825
02:26:35,216 --> 02:26:36,766
What did Mom say?

1826
02:26:38,507 --> 02:26:41,406
She's going to get Jiwan.

1827
02:26:41,407 --> 02:26:42,716
What?

1828
02:26:43,497 --> 02:26:44,437
Seriously...

1829
02:26:44,438 --> 02:26:45,766
Let's hurry up.

1830
02:26:49,727 --> 02:26:51,216
Jiwan, you!

1831
02:26:51,456 --> 02:26:52,327
Hello.

1832
02:26:52,328 --> 02:26:53,626
Just a second.

1833
02:26:54,067 --> 02:26:55,337
Hello.

1834
02:26:56,116 --> 02:26:58,876
It's an important meeting. This way.

1835
02:26:59,327 --> 02:27:01,396
Everything looks great.

1836
02:27:01,397 --> 02:27:05,096
I can see, now that I'm here.

1837
02:27:05,097 --> 02:27:08,726
You put up a makeshift
office near the farm.

1838
02:27:08,727 --> 02:27:12,605
It shows your concern for quality control.

1839
02:27:12,606 --> 02:27:13,896
I just need to sign here, yes?

1840
02:27:13,897 --> 02:27:15,296
Yes.

1841
02:27:20,776 --> 02:27:21,945
Thank you.

1842
02:27:21,946 --> 02:27:22,916
I hope this works out great.

1843
02:27:22,917 --> 02:27:23,947
Thank you.

1844
02:27:29,606 --> 02:27:30,666
Goodbye.

1845
02:27:30,667 --> 02:27:32,945
That guy

1846
02:27:32,946 --> 02:27:34,646
is great at many things.

1847
02:27:34,647 --> 02:27:36,496
He's amazing.

1848
02:27:36,497 --> 02:27:38,917
He performs better under pressure.

1849
02:27:40,296 --> 02:27:42,805
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

1850
02:27:42,806 --> 02:27:44,236
And it's such a hot day.

1851
02:27:44,237 --> 02:27:46,816
Let me get you something cool to drink.

1852
02:27:46,817 --> 02:27:48,136
Mr. Jang.

1853
02:27:54,227 --> 02:27:56,237
This is worth $30,000.

1854
02:28:00,767 --> 02:28:04,135
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

1855
02:28:04,136 --> 02:28:05,926
Hey, cut me some slack.

1856
02:28:05,927 --> 02:28:07,336
I was caught off guard.

1857
02:28:07,337 --> 02:28:08,666
It slipped out.

1858
02:28:08,667 --> 02:28:09,957
I can't believe you.

1859
02:28:10,257 --> 02:28:13,107
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

1860
02:28:14,386 --> 02:28:15,506
Director, you're here.

1861
02:28:15,507 --> 02:28:16,916
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

1862
02:28:16,917 --> 02:28:18,277
Yes.

1863
02:28:19,477 --> 02:28:20,767
What are you doing here?

1864
02:28:21,317 --> 02:28:22,715
What do you think?

1865
02:28:22,716 --> 02:28:24,535
They are working so hard on a hot day,

1866
02:28:24,536 --> 02:28:26,055
so I bought them Korean pork

1867
02:28:26,056 --> 02:28:28,656
to help them restore some energy.

1868
02:28:28,657 --> 02:28:31,535
Domestic is always the best.

1869
02:28:31,536 --> 02:28:33,926
Of course. You're a wise man.

1870
02:28:35,466 --> 02:28:38,125
Honey, don't just stand there.
Come and sit.

1871
02:28:38,126 --> 02:28:39,736
- Come here. / - Yeongju,
come and sit down.

1872
02:28:39,737 --> 02:28:41,205
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

1873
02:28:41,206 --> 02:28:42,305
Let me go get some more lettuce.

1874
02:28:42,306 --> 02:28:43,516
Okay.

1875
02:28:49,737 --> 02:28:50,945
Wait,

1876
02:28:50,946 --> 02:28:53,105
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

1877
02:28:53,106 --> 02:28:54,455
What's going on?

1878
02:28:54,456 --> 02:28:55,736
Oh, I can't believe you.

1879
02:28:55,737 --> 02:28:57,795
When? People might actually believe that.

1880
02:28:57,796 --> 02:28:59,896
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

1881
02:28:59,897 --> 02:29:03,365
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

1882
02:29:03,366 --> 02:29:06,156
so I bought him Korean pork,

1883
02:29:06,157 --> 02:29:08,096
to help him restore energy.

1884
02:29:08,097 --> 02:29:10,555
Why are you just sitting there?

1885
02:29:10,556 --> 02:29:12,336
Go and help wash the lettuce.

1886
02:29:12,337 --> 02:29:13,527
Go help Jiwan.

1887
02:29:13,977 --> 02:29:15,446
Okay.

1888
02:29:17,097 --> 02:29:20,875
I'm a great judge of character.

1889
02:29:20,876 --> 02:29:24,685
Mom, just have one spoonful.

1890
02:29:24,686 --> 02:29:25,556
Say ah.

1891
02:29:25,557 --> 02:29:28,535
I don't want any chicken porridge.

1892
02:29:28,536 --> 02:29:31,465
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

1893
02:29:31,466 --> 02:29:33,965
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

1894
02:29:33,966 --> 02:29:36,635
so you can restore energy, okay?

1895
02:29:36,636 --> 02:29:38,855
Just have one spoonful.

1896
02:29:38,856 --> 02:29:39,986
Say ah.

1897
02:29:45,917 --> 02:29:47,836
See?

1898
02:29:47,837 --> 02:29:50,726
You're upset because of what you said.

1899
02:29:50,727 --> 02:29:53,146
I didn't say anything wrong.

1900
02:29:53,147 --> 02:29:56,506
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

1901
02:29:56,507 --> 02:29:59,447
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

1902
02:30:01,157 --> 02:30:02,826
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

1903
02:30:02,827 --> 02:30:05,277
and meets someone nice.

1904
02:30:06,237 --> 02:30:08,556
I'm sure she will.

1905
02:30:09,147 --> 02:30:11,817
Couples form and break up all the time.

1906
02:30:13,946 --> 02:30:17,016
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

1907
02:30:17,017 --> 02:30:20,267
Jiwan has no time for that.

1908
02:30:22,407 --> 02:30:23,616
This?

1909
02:30:26,917 --> 02:30:28,417
You see,

1910
02:30:28,897 --> 02:30:32,526
here are the size and unit.

1911
02:30:35,786 --> 02:30:37,766
Hi.

1912
02:30:40,077 --> 02:30:43,286
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

1913
02:30:43,587 --> 02:30:45,736
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

1914
02:30:45,737 --> 02:30:47,417
But why are you here?

1915
02:30:49,856 --> 02:30:52,295
Oh, I'm stuffed.

1916
02:30:52,296 --> 02:30:56,176
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

1917
02:30:56,177 --> 02:30:57,656
You ate a lot of it.

1918
02:30:57,657 --> 02:30:59,157
Because it was delicious.

1919
02:31:02,116 --> 02:31:05,246
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

1920
02:31:05,247 --> 02:31:07,367
It's okay. I can go home alone.

1921
02:31:07,796 --> 02:31:08,716
Don't say that.

1922
02:31:08,717 --> 02:31:10,996
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

1923
02:31:10,997 --> 02:31:12,096
Take her home.

1924
02:31:12,097 --> 02:31:13,607
No, that's not going to happen.

1925
02:31:13,608 --> 02:31:15,166
Don't say that. Just go.

1926
02:31:15,167 --> 02:31:16,736
What are you two doing?

1927
02:31:16,737 --> 02:31:18,135
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

1928
02:31:18,136 --> 02:31:20,045
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

1929
02:31:20,046 --> 02:31:21,326
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

1930
02:31:21,327 --> 02:31:22,286
Okay.

1931
02:31:22,287 --> 02:31:23,647
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

1932
02:31:35,556 --> 02:31:37,686
Are those two dating?

1933
02:31:38,376 --> 02:31:40,496
They're not together yet,

1934
02:31:40,497 --> 02:31:43,417
but they are testing the waters.

1935
02:31:45,237 --> 02:31:47,916
It's frustrating to watch them.

1936
02:31:47,917 --> 02:31:49,546
Yeongju...

1937
02:31:50,276 --> 02:31:51,705
She's nice.

1938
02:31:51,706 --> 02:31:53,045
She is.

1939
02:31:53,046 --> 02:31:55,236
She's pretty and pleasant.

1940
02:31:55,237 --> 02:31:58,486
And she's a teacher.

1941
02:31:58,487 --> 02:31:59,635
Don't you think they look good together?

1942
02:31:59,636 --> 02:32:01,327
Yes, they do.

1943
02:32:11,776 --> 02:32:12,996
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

1944
02:32:37,347 --> 02:32:39,875
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

1945
02:32:39,876 --> 02:32:41,737
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

1946
02:32:43,427 --> 02:32:45,007
I'm just practicing.

1947
02:32:45,417 --> 02:32:46,957
Practicing?

1948
02:32:50,606 --> 02:32:52,775
Oh, I get it.

1949
02:32:52,776 --> 02:32:53,805
Girl...

1950
02:32:53,806 --> 02:32:57,195
You have a good eye.

1951
02:32:57,196 --> 02:32:58,006
What do you mean?

1952
02:32:58,007 --> 02:32:59,885
Jiwan.

1953
02:32:59,886 --> 02:33:01,566
Who cares about education?

1954
02:33:01,567 --> 02:33:05,066
To me, money trumps everything.

1955
02:33:05,067 --> 02:33:08,067
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

1956
02:33:10,587 --> 02:33:12,426
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

1957
02:33:12,427 --> 02:33:14,705
Eunsu is easy.

1958
02:33:14,706 --> 02:33:18,136
The grandmother-in-law
will become forgetful.

1959
02:33:18,747 --> 02:33:22,685
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

1960
02:33:22,686 --> 02:33:24,576
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

1961
02:33:24,577 --> 02:33:25,935
I told you it's not like that.

1962
02:33:25,936 --> 02:33:26,806
Just leave me alone.

1963
02:33:26,807 --> 02:33:29,695
How could I leave you alone?

1964
02:33:29,696 --> 02:33:31,346
You won't go on blind dates,

1965
02:33:31,347 --> 02:33:33,677
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

1966
02:33:34,727 --> 02:33:36,215
If it were me in the old days,

1967
02:33:36,216 --> 02:33:38,136
I would've already...

1968
02:33:38,886 --> 02:33:40,605
What's the use of giving you my looks?

1969
02:33:40,606 --> 02:33:42,256
Just look at yourself.

1970
02:33:42,257 --> 02:33:45,336
You're dressed like a tomboy,

1971
02:33:45,337 --> 02:33:47,215
and you haven't taken a shower.

1972
02:33:47,216 --> 02:33:50,166
You need to make yourself look pretty!

1973
02:33:50,167 --> 02:33:52,857
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

1974
02:33:52,858 --> 02:33:55,355
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

1975
02:33:55,356 --> 02:33:56,826
You have to look pretty!

1976
02:33:56,827 --> 02:33:58,687
What good will cooking do for you?

1977
02:33:58,688 --> 02:34:00,055
Besides your pretty face,

1978
02:34:00,056 --> 02:34:02,805
you got nothing from me!

1979
02:34:02,806 --> 02:34:05,116
What do you mean? Like this?

1980
02:34:08,077 --> 02:34:09,246
Oh, you're impossible.

1981
02:34:09,247 --> 02:34:11,697
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

1982
02:34:11,698 --> 02:34:14,567
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

1983
02:34:17,147 --> 02:34:18,215
Minja.

1984
02:34:18,216 --> 02:34:19,136
Oh!

1985
02:34:19,136 --> 02:34:20,106
Ms. Lee!

1986
02:34:20,107 --> 02:34:21,156
What are you doing here?

1987
02:34:21,157 --> 02:34:24,455
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

1988
02:34:24,456 --> 02:34:25,946
What about you?

1989
02:34:26,587 --> 02:34:29,437
Yeongju's been complaining
about neck pain, too.

1990
02:34:30,727 --> 02:34:32,006
Well,

1991
02:34:32,007 --> 02:34:35,617
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

1992
02:34:37,097 --> 02:34:38,426
I've given up on that.

1993
02:34:38,427 --> 02:34:39,777
How they feel about each
other is important,

1994
02:34:39,778 --> 02:34:41,506
not their background.

1995
02:34:41,956 --> 02:34:44,766
You're right!

1996
02:34:44,767 --> 02:34:49,947
But I heard you hold education very high.

1997
02:34:50,827 --> 02:34:54,115
If they're in love,
education doesn't matter.

1998
02:34:54,116 --> 02:34:57,157
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

1999
02:34:57,897 --> 02:35:03,017
But isn't a small family better?

2000
02:35:03,847 --> 02:35:07,185
I would prefer a small family,

2001
02:35:07,186 --> 02:35:08,586
but these days, as complicated as it is,

2002
02:35:08,587 --> 02:35:11,875
people don't live with married children.

2003
02:35:11,876 --> 02:35:14,296
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

2004
02:35:15,436 --> 02:35:16,996
But that's...

2005
02:35:16,997 --> 02:35:18,836
Well...

2006
02:35:18,837 --> 02:35:21,205
Old people don't live forever.

2007
02:35:21,206 --> 02:35:23,907
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

2008
02:35:24,436 --> 02:35:26,955
I'm not going to let my daughter

2009
02:35:26,956 --> 02:35:28,766
date anyone with a large family.

2010
02:35:28,767 --> 02:35:31,176
What if she gets stuck with them?

2011
02:35:31,177 --> 02:35:32,997
That won't be good.

2012
02:35:34,626 --> 02:35:37,806
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

2013
02:35:38,147 --> 02:35:39,916
As long as they live separately,

2014
02:35:39,917 --> 02:35:42,486
you don't mind a big family?

2015
02:35:42,487 --> 02:35:44,035
Of course not.

2016
02:35:44,036 --> 02:35:46,336
As long as they are in love.

2017
02:35:47,216 --> 02:35:48,106
Why do you ask?

2018
02:35:48,107 --> 02:35:51,896
You have someone in mind?

2019
02:35:51,897 --> 02:35:53,347
Of course.

2020
02:35:55,167 --> 02:35:57,327
- You do? / - Yes.

2021
02:36:08,497 --> 02:36:11,266
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

2022
02:36:11,267 --> 02:36:15,025
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

2023
02:36:15,026 --> 02:36:18,066
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

2024
02:36:18,067 --> 02:36:21,275
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

2025
02:36:21,276 --> 02:36:22,855
There are protocols for reporters...

2026
02:36:22,856 --> 02:36:24,445
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

2027
02:36:24,446 --> 02:36:27,166
former directors will be giving statements!

2028
02:36:27,167 --> 02:36:28,555
Tell me if it's true,

2029
02:36:28,556 --> 02:36:30,805
or if it's slander!

2030
02:36:30,806 --> 02:36:33,715
President Jang!

2031
02:36:33,716 --> 02:36:34,837
Please leave.

2032
02:36:38,147 --> 02:36:40,177
Refuse all interviews.

2033
02:36:40,796 --> 02:36:42,337
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

2034
02:36:43,227 --> 02:36:45,666
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

2035
02:36:45,667 --> 02:36:47,707
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

2036
02:36:49,577 --> 02:36:50,805
If he had all the evidence,

2037
02:36:50,806 --> 02:36:52,927
he would've written about it already.

2038
02:36:53,686 --> 02:36:56,176
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

2039
02:36:56,177 --> 02:36:59,525
I told you to find him, by any means!

2040
02:36:59,526 --> 02:37:00,366
What are you doing?

2041
02:37:00,367 --> 02:37:02,196
Is it that you can't or won't?

2042
02:37:04,556 --> 02:37:06,275
Seokjin was

2043
02:37:06,276 --> 02:37:09,016
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

2044
02:37:09,017 --> 02:37:11,017
and is still with us today.

2045
02:37:12,097 --> 02:37:15,305
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

2046
02:37:15,306 --> 02:37:17,716
whenever we reach a new milestone.

2047
02:37:19,106 --> 02:37:22,965
Hyeokju practically lived with us

2048
02:37:22,966 --> 02:37:24,647
at the factory.

2049
02:37:25,767 --> 02:37:28,226
So how could I

2050
02:37:28,227 --> 02:37:31,636
dig into their past, and make threats?

2051
02:37:32,616 --> 02:37:34,147
Taesu!

2052
02:37:37,577 --> 02:37:40,107
You've been paid off, too?

2053
02:37:42,567 --> 02:37:45,656
I know you met with Seokjin.

2054
02:37:45,657 --> 02:37:47,837
I wasn't sure.

2055
02:37:48,327 --> 02:37:49,646
So, what did you get from them?

2056
02:37:49,647 --> 02:37:52,577
How much did they pay you!

2057
02:37:53,206 --> 02:37:54,596
Taesu...

2058
02:37:54,597 --> 02:37:55,846
Get out.

2059
02:37:55,847 --> 02:37:56,827
You're fired!

2060
02:37:56,828 --> 02:37:58,197
Get lost!

2061
02:39:00,347 --> 02:39:01,997
Hyeondo,

2062
02:39:02,727 --> 02:39:05,455
I once told your father

2063
02:39:05,456 --> 02:39:07,747
to watch his back because of you.

2064
02:39:10,356 --> 02:39:12,736
And he said to me,

2065
02:39:14,397 --> 02:39:16,456
even if you betrayed him, that was okay.

2066
02:39:17,657 --> 02:39:19,636
Because you're his son.

2067
02:39:23,747 --> 02:39:25,767
Look after Taesu.

2068
02:39:27,987 --> 02:39:30,487
I can't seem to do it anymore.

2069
02:40:24,376 --> 02:40:27,726
Is this Mr. Han Yeongho of Daehan Daily?

2070
02:40:27,727 --> 02:40:29,597
This is Kim Jiwan.

2071
02:40:30,827 --> 02:40:34,216
Can we have that interview tomorrow?

2072
02:40:41,286 --> 02:40:42,907
Yes, Mr. Han.

2073
02:40:44,167 --> 02:40:45,847
I'm on my way.

2074
02:41:44,526 --> 02:41:46,086
Your father was going to

2075
02:41:47,296 --> 02:41:50,886
hand over his company to my father?

2076
02:41:54,167 --> 02:41:56,667
I couldn't understand him at first,

2077
02:41:58,946 --> 02:42:01,945
but now that I think about it,

2078
02:42:01,946 --> 02:42:03,876
I can understand him a little bit.

2079
02:42:17,427 --> 02:42:19,547
This is all the evidence I've collected.

2080
02:42:23,907 --> 02:42:25,796
Why are you giving them to me?

2081
02:42:30,936 --> 02:42:32,955
Why did you

2082
02:42:32,956 --> 02:42:35,116
give me that notebook?

2083
02:43:08,517 --> 02:43:09,837
Have you had a lot to drink?

2084
02:43:11,167 --> 02:43:14,687
You asked me here, so why are you late?

2085
02:43:19,306 --> 02:43:21,237
I met Jiwan.

2086
02:43:24,667 --> 02:43:26,947
Uncle Sangjun

2087
02:43:28,626 --> 02:43:31,936
was going to give you all his money?

2088
02:43:32,686 --> 02:43:34,596
That's a lie.

2089
02:43:35,366 --> 02:43:37,286
Right?

2090
02:43:40,747 --> 02:43:43,605
Who would actually do that?

2091
02:43:43,606 --> 02:43:45,935
Why would he give you his company

2092
02:43:45,936 --> 02:43:48,555
when he has a son and a family?

2093
02:43:48,556 --> 02:43:50,477
That's ridiculous.

2094
02:43:51,136 --> 02:43:52,956
You were just a friend.

2095
02:43:54,077 --> 02:43:55,867
Not his blood.

2096
02:43:59,897 --> 02:44:01,806
Don't you agree?

2097
02:44:03,446 --> 02:44:05,026
Yes.

2098
02:44:05,626 --> 02:44:07,606
I'm not his blood.

2099
02:44:10,497 --> 02:44:12,806
But,

2100
02:44:13,636 --> 02:44:16,385
even though I wasn't his blood,

2101
02:44:16,386 --> 02:44:20,025
Sangjun might have actually really

2102
02:44:20,026 --> 02:44:24,176
wanted to give me his company.

2103
02:44:27,167 --> 02:44:30,736
But why...

2104
02:44:30,737 --> 02:44:33,257
How could he trust me so much?

2105
02:45:10,727 --> 02:45:11,966
Jiwan.

2106
02:45:15,366 --> 02:45:18,705
Do you

2107
02:45:18,706 --> 02:45:21,586
remember Dad?

2108
02:45:24,616 --> 02:45:26,477
A little bit.

2109
02:45:29,587 --> 02:45:35,327
What kind of person was he?

2110
02:45:38,206 --> 02:45:41,397
He smiled at me whenever he saw me.

2111
02:45:48,946 --> 02:45:51,506
Why did

2112
02:45:53,376 --> 02:45:57,686
Dad trust a man like him?

2113
02:45:59,876 --> 02:46:02,477
He was so foolish.

2114
02:46:06,946 --> 02:46:09,926
You think so, too, don't you?

2115
02:47:20,626 --> 02:47:22,046
How have you been?

2116
02:47:34,927 --> 02:47:36,997
Don't turn bad.

2117
02:47:39,466 --> 02:47:42,136
That's not who you are, Hyeondo.

2118
02:47:53,067 --> 02:47:54,677
I should go.

2119
02:48:34,686 --> 02:48:35,926
The Korean Businessmen's Association

2120
02:48:35,927 --> 02:48:39,747
recommended you as a next chairperson.

2121
02:48:40,206 --> 02:48:44,136
You're to give an acceptance speech.

2122
02:48:45,587 --> 02:48:46,826
Okay.

2123
02:48:46,827 --> 02:48:48,306
I got it.

2124
02:48:48,886 --> 02:48:50,336
Oh, and

2125
02:48:50,337 --> 02:48:52,435
call my wife's lawyer,

2126
02:48:52,436 --> 02:48:54,455
and have him visit me here.

2127
02:48:54,456 --> 02:48:55,897
Yes, sir.

2128
02:49:03,987 --> 02:49:05,937
President Jang wants to see you

2129
02:49:05,938 --> 02:49:07,816
before going to court.

2130
02:49:09,116 --> 02:49:10,746
What is it about?

2131
02:49:10,747 --> 02:49:13,337
He said he will tell you in person.

2132
02:50:06,827 --> 02:50:10,025
You like the coffee here, don't you?

2133
02:50:10,026 --> 02:50:12,955
You didn't call me here for coffee.

2134
02:50:12,956 --> 02:50:14,956
What is this about?

2135
02:50:16,007 --> 02:50:18,216
I called you over to have a cup of coffee.

2136
02:50:19,067 --> 02:50:20,687
Excuse me.

2137
02:50:42,466 --> 02:50:45,705
I came because you like it here,

2138
02:50:45,706 --> 02:50:47,326
but to me, the company

2139
02:50:47,327 --> 02:50:50,477
vending machine coffee's the best.

2140
02:50:51,696 --> 02:50:55,756
You've always had cheap taste.

2141
02:50:55,757 --> 02:50:57,096
What?

2142
02:50:57,097 --> 02:50:59,277
You hate me because of my cheap taste?

2143
02:50:59,847 --> 02:51:02,226
No,

2144
02:51:02,227 --> 02:51:04,456
it was easy for me.

2145
02:51:07,147 --> 02:51:08,826
Successful men

2146
02:51:08,827 --> 02:51:12,375
always get a mistress first.

2147
02:51:12,376 --> 02:51:14,676
But

2148
02:51:14,677 --> 02:51:17,736
you have simple taste in everything.

2149
02:51:17,737 --> 02:51:19,885
Vending machine coffee, soju,

2150
02:51:19,886 --> 02:51:21,927
and roasted rice tea after meals.

2151
02:51:23,206 --> 02:51:25,796
And with women, only Jeong Sugyeong.

2152
02:51:27,556 --> 02:51:30,746
I did have simple taste,

2153
02:51:30,747 --> 02:51:33,347
but it was never cheap.

2154
02:51:36,237 --> 02:51:41,135
I loved having you

2155
02:51:41,136 --> 02:51:42,927
as my husband.

2156
02:51:45,757 --> 02:51:49,096
I respected you

2157
02:51:49,097 --> 02:51:53,917
more than anyone.

2158
02:51:58,767 --> 02:52:01,836
If you are willing to change,

2159
02:52:01,837 --> 02:52:04,767
nothing will change between us.

2160
02:52:12,786 --> 02:52:17,445
Will Jeong Sugyeong still love Jang Taesu

2161
02:52:17,446 --> 02:52:20,716
without his money and honor?

2162
02:52:24,487 --> 02:52:27,847
That's why it can't be, Ms. Jeong.

2163
02:52:38,747 --> 02:52:40,336
This is the divorce papers.

2164
02:52:40,337 --> 02:52:42,355
I already signed it,

2165
02:52:42,356 --> 02:52:44,386
so you take care of the rest.

2166
02:54:27,917 --> 02:54:31,136
Are you sure you want to let this go?

2167
02:54:32,267 --> 02:54:34,757
You won't regret it?

2168
02:54:36,577 --> 02:54:39,007
That was what Father wanted.

2169
02:54:40,247 --> 02:54:42,525
If President Jang

2170
02:54:42,526 --> 02:54:46,397
doesn't change his ways after finding out

2171
02:54:47,296 --> 02:54:49,997
what Father wanted, he'll
be more miserable.

2172
02:55:10,317 --> 02:55:13,455
Hello, everyone.

2173
02:55:13,456 --> 02:55:15,965
I'm Jang Taesu from Best Global,

2174
02:55:15,966 --> 02:55:19,407
who recently won Businessman of the Year.

2175
02:55:25,356 --> 02:55:29,256
There are many senior entrepreneurs

2176
02:55:29,257 --> 02:55:31,066
and colleagues who deserve the award,

2177
02:55:31,067 --> 02:55:32,795
so I feel a very big responsibility

2178
02:55:32,796 --> 02:55:35,036
to win this accolade.

2179
02:55:35,477 --> 02:55:40,146
And it's an honor to have the position

2180
02:55:40,147 --> 02:55:43,147
to represent all entrepreneurs.

2181
02:55:44,546 --> 02:55:48,355
Sitting here

2182
02:55:48,356 --> 02:55:50,966
brings back old memories.

2183
02:55:53,737 --> 02:55:59,177
I had a friend.

2184
02:55:59,767 --> 02:56:03,736
He trusted me when I had nothing,

2185
02:56:03,737 --> 02:56:08,317
and helped me get to where I am today.

2186
02:56:08,917 --> 02:56:11,135
He was the president of Taehu Industry

2187
02:56:11,136 --> 02:56:14,237
where Best Global began.

2188
02:56:17,616 --> 02:56:20,016
Kim Sangjun.

2189
02:56:21,956 --> 02:56:25,727
That was my friend's name.

2190
02:56:26,347 --> 02:56:29,666
He was naively trusting,

2191
02:56:29,667 --> 02:56:32,146
and honest

2192
02:56:32,147 --> 02:56:35,817
even to a fault.

2193
02:56:37,147 --> 02:56:39,885
I considered his company

2194
02:56:39,886 --> 02:56:43,337
as my own,

2195
02:56:44,657 --> 02:56:47,587
and worked hard.

2196
02:56:55,427 --> 02:56:58,685
But,

2197
02:56:58,686 --> 02:57:02,736
I

2198
02:57:02,737 --> 02:57:05,857
Stole...

2199
02:57:18,577 --> 02:57:20,997
All of his money.

2200
02:57:23,897 --> 02:57:25,366
What did he just say?

2201
02:57:43,647 --> 02:57:47,386
Yeongju, summarize this register, please.

2202
02:57:49,337 --> 02:57:50,957
May I help you?

2203
02:57:54,817 --> 02:57:57,006
Mr. Jang Hyeondo.

2204
02:57:57,007 --> 02:57:59,747
How dare you come here!

2205
02:58:00,837 --> 02:58:02,567
Jang Hyeondo?

2206
02:58:03,446 --> 02:58:05,545
You're that guy?

2207
02:58:05,546 --> 02:58:06,885
How dare you show your face here?

2208
02:58:06,886 --> 02:58:08,577
Get out.

2209
02:58:21,977 --> 02:58:24,167
I'm sorry.

2210
02:58:25,397 --> 02:58:28,626
That's all I can say.

2211
02:58:38,776 --> 02:58:40,317
Yes.

2212
02:58:41,206 --> 02:58:46,756
I tricked my trusting friend's family,

2213
02:58:46,757 --> 02:58:50,375
and bought their shares for pennies.

2214
02:58:50,376 --> 02:58:54,756
And I even kicked his family out

2215
02:58:54,757 --> 02:58:57,687
from their house.

2216
02:59:01,776 --> 02:59:04,516
And so I used

2217
02:59:04,517 --> 02:59:08,587
the stolen money,

2218
02:59:10,546 --> 02:59:14,716
and built my own company.

2219
02:59:25,507 --> 02:59:27,667
(Taehu Industry Stock
Certificate, $2.5 Million)

2220
03:00:08,706 --> 03:00:10,136
Dad!

2221
03:01:30,847 --> 03:01:33,805
(KBS 2TV, Weekend Drama, Bluebird's House)

2222
03:01:33,806 --> 03:01:34,757
I knew then,

2223
03:01:34,757 --> 03:01:35,687
(Best Global's Jang Taesu
Confesses to Embezzlement)

2224
03:01:36,077 --> 03:01:40,086
I would regret it for the rest of my life.

2225
03:01:40,087 --> 03:01:42,545
Sangjun

2226
03:01:42,546 --> 03:01:45,436
might have died because of me.

2227
03:01:46,636 --> 03:01:48,615
He's giving you what?

2228
03:01:48,616 --> 03:01:49,795
Stocks.

2229
03:01:49,796 --> 03:01:52,936
And he's resigning from his position.

2230
03:01:53,767 --> 03:01:56,726
Why are they so dense,

2231
03:01:56,727 --> 03:01:57,875
when I'm trying to help them?

2232
03:01:57,876 --> 03:01:59,885
They should at least try to

2233
03:01:59,886 --> 03:02:01,236
go on a few dates.

2234
03:02:01,237 --> 03:02:03,406
You're going to let Father be as he is?

2235
03:02:03,407 --> 03:02:06,647
Ma'am, get me a glass of ice water!

2236
03:02:50,186 --> 03:02:51,826
(Episode 49)

2237
03:02:51,827 --> 03:02:53,357
What is it?

2238
03:02:54,126 --> 03:02:56,596
You think with Lee Seokjin and some old

2239
03:02:56,597 --> 03:02:58,647
directors, you can turn the tables?

2240
03:02:59,097 --> 03:03:01,037
It's not that simple in the real world.

2241
03:03:03,487 --> 03:03:05,677
Is that your way of doing things?

2242
03:03:07,056 --> 03:03:09,635
Betraying a friend that trusts you,

2243
03:03:09,636 --> 03:03:12,157
and stealing all of his money?

2244
03:03:12,866 --> 03:03:15,846
Sangjun asked for this, do you know?

2245
03:03:15,847 --> 03:03:17,637
Is that why you wanted my father to die?

2246
03:03:17,638 --> 03:03:20,487
I said he was already
dead when I got there!

2247
03:03:23,767 --> 03:03:25,087
Sure.

2248
03:03:27,186 --> 03:03:30,326
Wherever you go and whomever you meet,

2249
03:03:30,327 --> 03:03:32,126
keep telling that story.

2250
03:03:33,077 --> 03:03:35,105
Even if

2251
03:03:35,106 --> 03:03:38,416
you made my father die,

2252
03:03:38,417 --> 03:03:40,545
don't ever speak of it.

2253
03:03:40,546 --> 03:03:42,167
Ever.

2254
03:03:43,647 --> 03:03:46,227
If not,

2255
03:03:46,907 --> 03:03:49,685
I would have to feel sorry for my father

2256
03:03:49,686 --> 03:03:52,166
for being too foolish

2257
03:03:52,167 --> 03:03:53,577
to have trusted you so much.

2258
03:03:59,077 --> 03:04:01,167
It was for you.

2259
03:04:03,337 --> 03:04:05,187
For you,

2260
03:04:06,827 --> 03:04:09,357
for an ingrate like you,

2261
03:04:11,647 --> 03:04:13,757
my father did all the work.

2262
03:04:19,487 --> 03:04:22,635
From the beginning, my father prepared

2263
03:04:22,636 --> 03:04:26,206
all the money and paperwork for you.

2264
03:04:27,667 --> 03:04:30,976
Even if you hadn't stolen the money,

2265
03:04:30,977 --> 03:04:34,355
if you just let things run its course,

2266
03:04:34,356 --> 03:04:36,866
you would've eventually gotten all of it.

2267
03:04:40,827 --> 03:04:44,625
I understand that you're an engineer,

2268
03:04:44,626 --> 03:04:46,646
but what about running the company?

2269
03:04:46,647 --> 03:04:49,285
Asking me to manage the money is...

2270
03:04:49,286 --> 03:04:52,566
If you do it, it'll be like I'm doing it.

2271
03:04:52,567 --> 03:04:53,826
Sangjun, still...

2272
03:04:53,827 --> 03:04:55,635
On top of that,

2273
03:04:55,636 --> 03:04:58,566
I don't know if I need to run the company.

2274
03:04:58,567 --> 03:04:59,715
I want to hire someone capable,

2275
03:04:59,716 --> 03:05:01,256
and have him run it the way he wants.

2276
03:05:01,257 --> 03:05:03,016
I can focus on technology development,

2277
03:05:03,017 --> 03:05:05,927
and he can help grow the company.

2278
03:05:15,157 --> 03:05:15,987
(President Kim Sangjun)

2279
03:05:15,988 --> 03:05:17,277
Sangjun.

2280
03:05:17,677 --> 03:05:19,266
Sangjun!

2281
03:05:19,267 --> 03:05:20,547
Hey, Sangjun!

2282
03:05:48,157 --> 03:05:50,286
(Taehu Industry Stock
Certificate, $2.5 Million)

2283
03:06:27,757 --> 03:06:31,947
Talk about lying through your teeth.

2284
03:06:32,397 --> 03:06:34,646
Who in the world

2285
03:06:34,647 --> 03:06:36,256
gives all his money to his friend

2286
03:06:36,257 --> 03:06:38,746
when he has his own family,

2287
03:06:38,747 --> 03:06:41,795
his own parents, and a wife?

2288
03:06:41,796 --> 03:06:44,067
I don't understand, either.

2289
03:06:45,567 --> 03:06:48,157
If he was alive, I'd love to ask him

2290
03:06:49,786 --> 03:06:52,196
why he trusted someone like you.

2291
03:06:53,897 --> 03:06:56,365
What kind of crazy idiot would

2292
03:06:56,366 --> 03:06:59,916
trust his friend with all his money?

2293
03:07:02,036 --> 03:07:05,456
You think I would believe that nonsense?

2294
03:07:07,247 --> 03:07:09,407
Taehu Industry's attorney Hong Mungi.

2295
03:07:11,366 --> 03:07:13,535
He was one of the people you fired

2296
03:07:13,536 --> 03:07:16,006
when Taehu Industry filed for bankruptcy.

2297
03:07:17,577 --> 03:07:19,527
You can ask him.

2298
03:08:22,296 --> 03:08:25,106
(President Kim Sangjun)

2299
03:08:25,267 --> 03:08:27,497
(Registration Certificate,
Owner Jang Taesu)

2300
03:08:32,007 --> 03:08:34,555
Taesu, what time will you be back?

2301
03:08:34,556 --> 03:08:38,025
Well, I think I'll finish around 5.

2302
03:08:38,026 --> 03:08:39,896
I'll see you then.

2303
03:08:39,897 --> 03:08:42,435
I have something to tell you.

2304
03:08:42,436 --> 03:08:44,176
What is it? Tell me now.

2305
03:08:44,177 --> 03:08:45,097
I'll tell you later.

2306
03:08:45,098 --> 03:08:46,676
Don't be late.

2307
03:08:46,677 --> 03:08:49,756
I have a favor to ask you,

2308
03:08:49,757 --> 03:08:52,216
and something to give you.

2309
03:09:30,366 --> 03:09:32,456
Your mother's waiting.

2310
03:09:41,556 --> 03:09:44,205
If

2311
03:09:44,206 --> 03:09:46,965
Anything happens to me,

2312
03:09:46,966 --> 03:09:48,727
ask Taesu for help.

2313
03:09:51,417 --> 03:09:53,697
Don't say such a thing.

2314
03:09:54,886 --> 03:09:56,587
I'm saying, just in case.

2315
03:10:11,776 --> 03:10:13,236
Hello?

2316
03:10:23,356 --> 03:10:26,647
Who is this, so early in the morning?

2317
03:10:28,866 --> 03:10:30,706
Do you remember me?

2318
03:10:32,147 --> 03:10:33,407
President Jang!

2319
03:10:34,556 --> 03:10:35,846
- Come in. / - No, no, wait.

2320
03:10:35,847 --> 03:10:37,657
My coming in isn't important right now.

2321
03:10:37,987 --> 03:10:42,525
Did you meet Sangjun's son Kim Jiwan?

2322
03:10:42,526 --> 03:10:44,096
Did you see him a few days ago?

2323
03:10:44,097 --> 03:10:48,467
Yes, I met Jiwan a few days ago.

2324
03:10:49,296 --> 03:10:51,846
What did you two talk about?

2325
03:10:52,507 --> 03:10:55,435
He asked about the financial state

2326
03:10:55,436 --> 03:10:59,096
of Mr. Kim when he passed away.

2327
03:10:59,097 --> 03:11:04,367
Is there any legal problems?

2328
03:11:05,956 --> 03:11:07,355
Yes,

2329
03:11:07,356 --> 03:11:09,666
when Sangjun died,

2330
03:11:09,667 --> 03:11:11,785
what happened to his assets?

2331
03:11:11,786 --> 03:11:15,326
You know that better than I do.

2332
03:11:15,327 --> 03:11:18,385
He turned everything into cash,

2333
03:11:18,386 --> 03:11:21,096
and invested it into his company.

2334
03:11:21,097 --> 03:11:22,365
Invested it,

2335
03:11:22,366 --> 03:11:23,646
yes.

2336
03:11:23,647 --> 03:11:24,976
Yes, that's right.

2337
03:11:24,977 --> 03:11:26,385
He invested all of it.

2338
03:11:26,386 --> 03:11:28,596
He didn't plan on giving it to me, right?

2339
03:11:28,597 --> 03:11:35,775
He said he was making you the president.

2340
03:11:35,776 --> 03:11:40,216
Isn't that the same thing?

2341
03:11:48,216 --> 03:11:52,986
I want to give Taesu a chance.

2342
03:11:52,987 --> 03:11:54,535
I want to make it

2343
03:11:54,536 --> 03:11:57,295
so that he can make this company grow.

2344
03:11:57,296 --> 03:11:58,965
Mr. Kim,

2345
03:11:58,966 --> 03:12:01,587
what about your family?

2346
03:12:02,196 --> 03:12:06,026
Putting him in charge of the money is...

2347
03:12:06,897 --> 03:12:09,935
This investment is for my family.

2348
03:12:09,936 --> 03:12:11,506
Excuse me?

2349
03:12:13,327 --> 03:12:15,406
I'm not sure

2350
03:12:15,407 --> 03:12:17,685
how much longer

2351
03:12:17,686 --> 03:12:19,486
my heart will last.

2352
03:12:20,856 --> 03:12:24,836
Without me, what will happen to my mother,

2353
03:12:24,837 --> 03:12:26,347
my wife, and kids?

2354
03:12:28,116 --> 03:12:30,875
Anyone can talk my mother into signing

2355
03:12:30,876 --> 03:12:33,435
any document they want, and my wife

2356
03:12:33,436 --> 03:12:37,496
does not know how to deal with my mother.

2357
03:12:37,497 --> 03:12:42,016
I need someone to be there for my family.

2358
03:12:42,017 --> 03:12:45,385
Money aside, I know Taesu will

2359
03:12:45,386 --> 03:12:48,186
take great care of my family.

2360
03:12:49,407 --> 03:12:53,927
I know what kind of man he is.

2361
03:13:02,567 --> 03:13:05,427
President Jang...

2362
03:13:09,647 --> 03:13:11,816
You,

2363
03:13:11,817 --> 03:13:13,586
you're lying, aren't you?

2364
03:13:13,587 --> 03:13:14,826
How much money did Kim Jiwan give you?

2365
03:13:14,827 --> 03:13:16,516
How much did it take to pay you off?

2366
03:13:16,517 --> 03:13:18,027
President Jang...

2367
03:13:32,626 --> 03:13:35,006
I need to see you right now.

2368
03:13:35,007 --> 03:13:36,305
Come to my office.

2369
03:13:36,306 --> 03:13:38,545
I'm not interested in seeing you.

2370
03:13:38,546 --> 03:13:39,876
I'm hanging up.

2371
03:13:46,286 --> 03:13:47,737
Take me to Kim Jiwan's apartment.

2372
03:14:18,397 --> 03:14:20,305
I just

2373
03:14:20,306 --> 03:14:23,716
met with Taehu Industry's company lawyer.

2374
03:14:25,706 --> 03:14:27,486
Then you must've heard everything.

2375
03:14:27,487 --> 03:14:28,917
Yes.

2376
03:14:31,136 --> 03:14:35,766
You mean you heard about Sangjun?

2377
03:14:36,686 --> 03:14:39,865
Your family's become quite crafty.

2378
03:14:39,866 --> 03:14:41,635
Was it money, or something else?

2379
03:14:41,636 --> 03:14:44,926
How did you make him lie to me like that?

2380
03:14:44,927 --> 03:14:47,367
I remember him as a man of integrity,

2381
03:14:47,368 --> 03:14:49,356
so how did you buy him off?

2382
03:14:51,897 --> 03:14:55,746
You're well-prepared to taint my name.

2383
03:14:55,747 --> 03:14:58,305
Turning Sangjun into a saint

2384
03:14:58,306 --> 03:15:00,695
will make me look dirtier and pettier.

2385
03:15:00,696 --> 03:15:02,135
On top of stealing money, I'd become

2386
03:15:02,136 --> 03:15:06,185
a bastard who betrayed his best friend.

2387
03:15:06,186 --> 03:15:08,226
Is that the plan?

2388
03:15:08,227 --> 03:15:10,775
Telling the world how dirty and petty I am?

2389
03:15:10,776 --> 03:15:13,166
That's what you're afraid of?

2390
03:15:16,606 --> 03:15:18,795
I'm relieved.

2391
03:15:18,796 --> 03:15:22,227
At least you know what you did was wrong.

2392
03:15:26,657 --> 03:15:28,847
Why did you do it?

2393
03:15:30,886 --> 03:15:33,596
You're not that type of person.

2394
03:15:34,407 --> 03:15:36,836
You valued people,

2395
03:15:36,837 --> 03:15:39,407
and you were very understanding.

2396
03:15:40,946 --> 03:15:44,455
So Sangjun, Mother, and I

2397
03:15:44,456 --> 03:15:47,766
trusted you with everything.

2398
03:15:47,767 --> 03:15:50,477
You were upright and kindhearted.

2399
03:15:53,866 --> 03:15:55,946
What happened to you?

2400
03:15:58,046 --> 03:16:02,455
How did you end up here like this,

2401
03:16:02,456 --> 03:16:07,086
doubting Sangjun's intentions, Mr. Jang?

2402
03:16:17,276 --> 03:16:19,965
Find evidence on how Kim Jiwan

2403
03:16:19,966 --> 03:16:21,445
bought that lawyer off.

2404
03:16:21,446 --> 03:16:22,605
Taesu, what if...

2405
03:16:22,606 --> 03:16:24,176
What if, what?

2406
03:16:24,177 --> 03:16:26,035
You think it might be true?

2407
03:16:26,036 --> 03:16:27,956
But if it's true, I'm...

2408
03:16:33,097 --> 03:16:34,676
No.

2409
03:16:34,677 --> 03:16:37,836
I'm sure there's evidence of him lying.

2410
03:16:37,837 --> 03:16:41,016
What do you think Kim Jiwan offered him?

2411
03:16:41,017 --> 03:16:41,827
Wait...

2412
03:16:41,828 --> 03:16:43,365
Wait, this means

2413
03:16:43,366 --> 03:16:46,436
he can buy my people off, too.

2414
03:16:47,856 --> 03:16:50,586
What are you waiting for? Go find it!

2415
03:16:51,597 --> 03:16:52,887
Yes, sir.

2416
03:17:02,597 --> 03:17:05,297
I'm Ha Yeongho of Daehan Daily.

2417
03:17:06,177 --> 03:17:07,236
I'm Kim Jiwan.

2418
03:17:07,237 --> 03:17:08,536
Have a seat.

2419
03:17:13,356 --> 03:17:16,846
I heard the news from a former employee.

2420
03:17:16,847 --> 03:17:19,226
You've been contacting former directors?

2421
03:17:19,227 --> 03:17:20,685
How many people have you met with?

2422
03:17:20,686 --> 03:17:22,296
About twenty.

2423
03:17:23,167 --> 03:17:24,945
And I've been preparing

2424
03:17:24,946 --> 03:17:26,906
the recordings of their accounts.

2425
03:17:26,907 --> 03:17:28,266
I think I can report the story right away

2426
03:17:28,267 --> 03:17:31,025
if I had a copy of those recordings.

2427
03:17:31,026 --> 03:17:33,375
Can you give me a copy?

2428
03:17:33,376 --> 03:17:34,635
Of course.

2429
03:17:34,636 --> 03:17:36,977
I'll call you once I'm done sorting them.

2430
03:18:39,186 --> 03:18:41,786
Can't fall asleep?

2431
03:18:44,306 --> 03:18:46,806
I can't seem to understand Father.

2432
03:18:48,306 --> 03:18:51,766
Why did he try to put someone like

2433
03:18:51,767 --> 03:18:54,407
Jang Taesu in charge of his money?

2434
03:18:56,237 --> 03:18:57,445
That was so foolish.

2435
03:18:57,446 --> 03:18:58,826
Jiwan.

2436
03:19:00,966 --> 03:19:03,606
Don't blame your father.

2437
03:19:04,167 --> 03:19:07,635
Back then, the only person he could trust

2438
03:19:07,636 --> 03:19:10,177
was Mr. Jang Taesu.

2439
03:19:11,327 --> 03:19:14,605
With his health deteriorating,

2440
03:19:14,606 --> 03:19:18,196
your father was afraid of the future.

2441
03:19:18,856 --> 03:19:21,586
And he thought

2442
03:19:21,587 --> 03:19:26,156
Mr. Jang Taesu could look after us.

2443
03:19:26,157 --> 03:19:28,327
He was wrong.

2444
03:19:29,116 --> 03:19:31,166
He trusted the man

2445
03:19:31,167 --> 03:19:33,805
who stole all his money the day he died.

2446
03:19:33,806 --> 03:19:36,666
If it were me,

2447
03:19:36,667 --> 03:19:38,417
I would've trusted Mr. Jang Taesu, too.

2448
03:19:39,796 --> 03:19:42,685
He was a different man

2449
03:19:42,686 --> 03:19:44,896
from who he is now.

2450
03:19:44,897 --> 03:19:46,945
And that's why I can't forgive him.

2451
03:19:46,946 --> 03:19:49,025
As a human being,

2452
03:19:49,026 --> 03:19:50,166
you cannot betray someone

2453
03:19:50,167 --> 03:19:51,987
who trusts you.

2454
03:21:36,847 --> 03:21:38,617
Hyeondo.

2455
03:21:40,856 --> 03:21:45,276
Why not resign from your father's company?

2456
03:21:49,247 --> 03:21:53,626
I'll look into another job for you.

2457
03:21:57,356 --> 03:21:59,236
I should go to work.

2458
03:22:10,126 --> 03:22:12,375
Sugyeong came to see you?

2459
03:22:12,376 --> 03:22:15,796
She really begged for your forgiveness?

2460
03:22:16,907 --> 03:22:20,237
Sugyeong looked really bad.

2461
03:22:21,347 --> 03:22:23,605
I think she's miserable.

2462
03:22:23,606 --> 03:22:25,156
She should be.

2463
03:22:25,157 --> 03:22:26,605
Of course.

2464
03:22:26,606 --> 03:22:29,716
If she's not, she's not human.

2465
03:22:30,407 --> 03:22:34,035
Wait, but why do you sound so sad?

2466
03:22:34,036 --> 03:22:35,606
What?

2467
03:22:36,356 --> 03:22:39,736
Seeing her miserable made you soft?

2468
03:22:39,737 --> 03:22:42,086
Oh, my.

2469
03:22:42,087 --> 03:22:44,337
You sure are a saint.

2470
03:22:44,987 --> 03:22:46,836
She's going through a rough time after

2471
03:22:46,837 --> 03:22:50,096
a life of luxury, and you feel sorry?

2472
03:22:50,097 --> 03:22:53,357
You're the one I feel sorry for.

2473
03:22:54,407 --> 03:22:59,935
It seems as though Hyeondo is sick.

2474
03:22:59,936 --> 03:23:01,736
He's at the hospital.

2475
03:23:01,737 --> 03:23:03,756
Hyeondo?

2476
03:23:03,757 --> 03:23:05,377
How could a child be healthy

2477
03:23:05,378 --> 03:23:07,705
when his parents have no morals?

2478
03:23:07,706 --> 03:23:11,477
Karma passes down to children.

2479
03:23:14,267 --> 03:23:17,977
Thank you for helping me in Russia.

2480
03:23:18,597 --> 03:23:20,107
How could I say no to you?

2481
03:23:20,108 --> 03:23:22,416
I had to do it.

2482
03:23:22,417 --> 03:23:23,805
So I was thinking,

2483
03:23:23,806 --> 03:23:25,736
I heard you might end up

2484
03:23:25,737 --> 03:23:28,545
taking over the company.

2485
03:23:28,546 --> 03:23:30,816
There's an idea

2486
03:23:30,817 --> 03:23:34,336
I've been developing for five years,

2487
03:23:34,337 --> 03:23:37,156
and going to Russia gave me

2488
03:23:37,157 --> 03:23:39,226
reaffirmation on my idea.

2489
03:23:39,227 --> 03:23:41,646
So I was wondering

2490
03:23:41,647 --> 03:23:44,896
if you could give me a chance

2491
03:23:44,897 --> 03:23:47,347
to present that idea to you.

2492
03:23:51,227 --> 03:23:52,927
Please don't joke around with me.

2493
03:23:53,616 --> 03:23:55,076
I'm not...

2494
03:23:55,077 --> 03:23:58,756
Yes, I know I was hard on you,

2495
03:23:58,757 --> 03:24:00,836
and made your life difficult.

2496
03:24:00,837 --> 03:24:04,775
I saw talent when I saw you, so,

2497
03:24:04,776 --> 03:24:06,805
yes, like in Chinese novels,

2498
03:24:06,806 --> 03:24:08,355
in order to make someone a hero,

2499
03:24:08,356 --> 03:24:10,435
people around him

2500
03:24:10,436 --> 03:24:13,226
create hardships for him.

2501
03:24:13,227 --> 03:24:15,176
All Chinese heroes are like that.

2502
03:24:15,177 --> 03:24:17,305
They prevail over and over again,

2503
03:24:17,306 --> 03:24:18,296
and accomplish...

2504
03:24:18,297 --> 03:24:19,896
It's okay.

2505
03:24:19,897 --> 03:24:20,827
No, I...

2506
03:24:20,828 --> 03:24:22,867
I said it's okay!

2507
03:24:23,536 --> 03:24:24,846
Why do you keep bugging me!

2508
03:24:24,847 --> 03:24:26,346
I said it's okay!

2509
03:24:26,347 --> 03:24:27,887
Something great.

2510
03:24:30,237 --> 03:24:31,566
I think you're mistaken.

2511
03:24:31,567 --> 03:24:33,025
It's okay.

2512
03:24:33,026 --> 03:24:35,386
Sorry for cutting you off, but you're...

2513
03:24:35,956 --> 03:24:37,346
No, I'm not mistaken.

2514
03:24:37,347 --> 03:24:39,305
I think you're mistaken.

2515
03:24:39,306 --> 03:24:42,177
It's not like that. Just think about it.

2516
03:24:42,657 --> 03:24:45,486
When you asked me for a favor like that,

2517
03:24:45,487 --> 03:24:49,257
wasn't it because we are close?

2518
03:24:50,296 --> 03:24:51,926
- Yes. / - Right?

2519
03:24:51,927 --> 03:24:57,486
So since we share a special relationship,

2520
03:24:57,487 --> 03:24:58,456
let me present it in a special...

2521
03:24:58,457 --> 03:24:59,567
Jiwan.

2522
03:24:59,977 --> 03:25:01,045
Hi, Eunsu.

2523
03:25:01,046 --> 03:25:02,375
Ms. Han Eunsu!

2524
03:25:02,376 --> 03:25:04,476
Oh? Hello.

2525
03:25:04,477 --> 03:25:05,966
What are you doing here?

2526
03:25:08,196 --> 03:25:09,766
Huh?

2527
03:25:11,837 --> 03:25:13,857
She's my little sister.

2528
03:25:14,856 --> 03:25:16,375
Your real sister?

2529
03:25:16,376 --> 03:25:17,497
Yes.

2530
03:25:17,817 --> 03:25:22,446
But her last name's Han, and yours is Kim.

2531
03:25:24,087 --> 03:25:25,635
Jiwan, Eunsu.

2532
03:25:25,636 --> 03:25:27,526
- Hi, Aunt. / - Hi.

2533
03:25:28,116 --> 03:25:29,125
Remember?

2534
03:25:29,126 --> 03:25:31,816
This is Mr. Yun, my former team leader.

2535
03:25:31,817 --> 03:25:33,205
- Hello. / - She's my aunt.

2536
03:25:33,206 --> 03:25:34,166
Oh, Aunt.

2537
03:25:34,167 --> 03:25:37,707
Hello, I am Yun Oyong.

2538
03:25:39,227 --> 03:25:40,275
Hi.

2539
03:25:40,276 --> 03:25:43,525
I'm Park Haengsuk.

2540
03:25:43,526 --> 03:25:44,746
Excuse me?

2541
03:25:44,747 --> 03:25:46,586
Park...

2542
03:25:46,587 --> 03:25:50,367
You're his aunt, but
your last name is Park?

2543
03:25:52,097 --> 03:25:57,416
Kim, Han and Park.

2544
03:25:57,417 --> 03:26:00,037
A family with different last names?

2545
03:26:05,376 --> 03:26:08,006
What happened?

2546
03:26:08,007 --> 03:26:09,586
Why is that office empty?

2547
03:26:09,587 --> 03:26:12,305
All the desks and chairs are gone.

2548
03:26:12,306 --> 03:26:13,906
Oh, that office?

2549
03:26:13,907 --> 03:26:15,406
They moved out.

2550
03:26:15,407 --> 03:26:17,156
They moved out?

2551
03:26:17,157 --> 03:26:19,336
Where did they go?

2552
03:26:19,337 --> 03:26:21,055
Where are my daughter and husband?

2553
03:26:21,056 --> 03:26:26,056
I heard they're pitching a tent at a farm.

2554
03:26:28,856 --> 03:26:30,406
A, a tent?

2555
03:26:37,267 --> 03:26:38,385
Oh,

2556
03:26:38,386 --> 03:26:41,875
I think we need to get a phone line fast.

2557
03:26:41,876 --> 03:26:43,156
When is the phone guy coming?

2558
03:26:43,157 --> 03:26:45,016
He'll be here at 3.

2559
03:26:45,017 --> 03:26:47,006
Where should the line go?

2560
03:26:47,007 --> 03:26:48,517
I'll find a spot.

2561
03:26:48,897 --> 03:26:50,206
I'll take that, Yeongju.

2562
03:26:57,296 --> 03:26:59,346
You shouldn't bite off
more than you can chew,

2563
03:26:59,347 --> 03:27:00,976
and mingle with your own kind!

2564
03:27:00,977 --> 03:27:04,176
You're suffering because of Jiwan!

2565
03:27:04,177 --> 03:27:06,076
It's my fault for signing a contract

2566
03:27:06,077 --> 03:27:08,646
that says the owner can
evict us at any time.

2567
03:27:08,647 --> 03:27:10,355
How dare you side with Jiwan!

2568
03:27:10,356 --> 03:27:12,326
I'm going to get him for this!

2569
03:27:13,456 --> 03:27:14,567
Honey, Mi...

2570
03:27:17,927 --> 03:27:19,477
What did Mom say?

2571
03:27:21,216 --> 03:27:24,115
She's going to get Jiwan.

2572
03:27:24,116 --> 03:27:25,426
What?

2573
03:27:26,206 --> 03:27:27,147
Seriously...

2574
03:27:27,148 --> 03:27:28,477
Let's hurry up.

2575
03:27:32,436 --> 03:27:33,926
Jiwan, you!

2576
03:27:34,167 --> 03:27:35,037
Hello.

2577
03:27:35,038 --> 03:27:36,336
Just a second.

2578
03:27:36,776 --> 03:27:38,046
Hello.

2579
03:27:38,827 --> 03:27:41,587
It's an important meeting. This way.

2580
03:27:42,036 --> 03:27:44,105
Everything looks great.

2581
03:27:44,106 --> 03:27:47,805
I can see, now that I'm here.

2582
03:27:47,806 --> 03:27:51,435
You put up a makeshift
office near the farm.

2583
03:27:51,436 --> 03:27:55,316
It shows your concern for quality control.

2584
03:27:55,317 --> 03:27:56,607
I just need to sign here, yes?

2585
03:27:56,608 --> 03:27:58,006
Yes.

2586
03:28:03,487 --> 03:28:04,656
Thank you.

2587
03:28:04,657 --> 03:28:05,626
I hope this works out great.

2588
03:28:05,627 --> 03:28:06,657
Thank you.

2589
03:28:12,317 --> 03:28:13,375
Goodbye.

2590
03:28:13,376 --> 03:28:15,656
That guy

2591
03:28:15,657 --> 03:28:17,355
is great at many things.

2592
03:28:17,356 --> 03:28:19,205
He's amazing.

2593
03:28:19,206 --> 03:28:21,626
He performs better under pressure.

2594
03:28:23,007 --> 03:28:25,516
Ms. Lee, it must've been hard to find us.

2595
03:28:25,517 --> 03:28:26,947
And it's such a hot day.

2596
03:28:26,948 --> 03:28:29,525
Let me get you something cool to drink.

2597
03:28:29,526 --> 03:28:30,846
Mr. Jang.

2598
03:28:36,936 --> 03:28:38,946
This is worth $30,000.

2599
03:28:43,477 --> 03:28:46,846
Dad, why did you say it was Jiwan's fault?

2600
03:28:46,847 --> 03:28:48,635
Hey, cut me some slack.

2601
03:28:48,636 --> 03:28:50,045
I was caught off guard.

2602
03:28:50,046 --> 03:28:51,375
It slipped out.

2603
03:28:51,376 --> 03:28:52,667
I can't believe you.

2604
03:28:52,966 --> 03:28:55,817
It's cooked. Yes, have some.

2605
03:28:57,097 --> 03:28:58,217
Director, you're here.

2606
03:28:58,218 --> 03:28:59,625
- Mr. Kang, you're here. / - Honey.

2607
03:28:59,626 --> 03:29:00,987
Yes.

2608
03:29:02,186 --> 03:29:03,477
What are you doing here?

2609
03:29:04,026 --> 03:29:05,426
What do you think?

2610
03:29:05,427 --> 03:29:07,246
They are working so hard on a hot day,

2611
03:29:07,247 --> 03:29:08,766
so I bought them Korean pork

2612
03:29:08,767 --> 03:29:11,365
to help them restore some energy.

2613
03:29:11,366 --> 03:29:14,246
Domestic is always the best.

2614
03:29:14,247 --> 03:29:16,636
Of course. You're a wise man.

2615
03:29:18,177 --> 03:29:20,836
Honey, don't just stand there.
Come and sit.

2616
03:29:20,837 --> 03:29:22,447
- Come here. / - Yeongju,
come and sit down.

2617
03:29:22,448 --> 03:29:23,916
Yes, Yeongju, come and eat.

2618
03:29:23,917 --> 03:29:25,016
Let me go get some more lettuce.

2619
03:29:25,017 --> 03:29:26,227
Okay.

2620
03:29:32,446 --> 03:29:33,656
Wait,

2621
03:29:33,657 --> 03:29:35,816
weren't you mad at Jiwan?

2622
03:29:35,817 --> 03:29:37,166
What's going on?

2623
03:29:37,167 --> 03:29:38,447
Oh, I can't believe you.

2624
03:29:38,448 --> 03:29:40,506
When? People might actually believe that.

2625
03:29:40,507 --> 03:29:42,607
Why would I talk badly about Jiwan?

2626
03:29:42,608 --> 03:29:46,076
When I came here, Jiwan was doing great,

2627
03:29:46,077 --> 03:29:48,865
so I bought him Korean pork,

2628
03:29:48,866 --> 03:29:50,805
to help him restore energy.

2629
03:29:50,806 --> 03:29:53,266
Why are you just sitting there?

2630
03:29:53,267 --> 03:29:55,047
Go and help wash the lettuce.

2631
03:29:55,048 --> 03:29:56,237
Go help Jiwan.

2632
03:29:56,686 --> 03:29:58,156
Okay.

2633
03:29:59,806 --> 03:30:03,586
I'm a great judge of character.

2634
03:30:03,587 --> 03:30:07,396
Mom, just have one spoonful.

2635
03:30:07,397 --> 03:30:08,267
Say ah.

2636
03:30:08,268 --> 03:30:11,246
I don't want any chicken porridge.

2637
03:30:11,247 --> 03:30:14,176
It's not just chicken. It has ginseng, too.

2638
03:30:14,177 --> 03:30:16,676
You need to eat warm food in the summer,

2639
03:30:16,677 --> 03:30:19,346
so you can restore energy, okay?

2640
03:30:19,347 --> 03:30:21,566
Just have one spoonful.

2641
03:30:21,567 --> 03:30:22,696
Say ah.

2642
03:30:28,626 --> 03:30:30,545
See?

2643
03:30:30,546 --> 03:30:33,435
You're upset because of what you said.

2644
03:30:33,436 --> 03:30:35,855
I didn't say anything wrong.

2645
03:30:35,856 --> 03:30:39,215
Imagine how Seonhui and Eunsu must feel.

2646
03:30:39,216 --> 03:30:42,157
You're worried about Eunsu, aren't you?

2647
03:30:43,866 --> 03:30:45,535
I hope she gets over Hyeondo,

2648
03:30:45,536 --> 03:30:47,987
and meets someone nice.

2649
03:30:48,946 --> 03:30:51,266
I'm sure she will.

2650
03:30:51,856 --> 03:30:54,526
Couples form and break up all the time.

2651
03:30:56,657 --> 03:30:59,726
Jiwan doesn't have a girlfriend?

2652
03:30:59,727 --> 03:31:02,977
Jiwan has no time for that.

2653
03:31:05,116 --> 03:31:06,326
This?

2654
03:31:09,626 --> 03:31:11,126
You see,

2655
03:31:11,606 --> 03:31:15,236
here are the size and unit.

2656
03:31:18,497 --> 03:31:20,477
Hi.

2657
03:31:22,786 --> 03:31:25,996
Maybe I shouldn't have come.

2658
03:31:26,296 --> 03:31:28,445
Don't say that. I'm glad you're here.

2659
03:31:28,446 --> 03:31:30,126
But why are you here?

2660
03:31:32,567 --> 03:31:35,006
Oh, I'm stuffed.

2661
03:31:35,007 --> 03:31:38,885
You must really love spicy chicken stew.

2662
03:31:38,886 --> 03:31:40,365
You ate a lot of it.

2663
03:31:40,366 --> 03:31:41,866
Because it was delicious.

2664
03:31:44,827 --> 03:31:47,955
It's late, so take Yeongju home.

2665
03:31:47,956 --> 03:31:50,077
It's okay. I can go home alone.

2666
03:31:50,507 --> 03:31:51,427
Don't say that.

2667
03:31:51,428 --> 03:31:53,707
It's late. What if you get kidnapped?

2668
03:31:53,708 --> 03:31:54,805
Take her home.

2669
03:31:54,806 --> 03:31:56,316
No, that's not going to happen.

2670
03:31:56,317 --> 03:31:57,875
Don't say that. Just go.

2671
03:31:57,876 --> 03:31:59,445
What are you two doing?

2672
03:31:59,446 --> 03:32:00,846
Let's go. I'll walk you home.

2673
03:32:00,847 --> 03:32:02,756
- What? / - Go home, and go to bed.

2674
03:32:02,757 --> 03:32:04,035
- Let's go, Yeongju. / - Bye.

2675
03:32:04,036 --> 03:32:04,996
Okay.

2676
03:32:04,997 --> 03:32:06,357
- Bye. / - Goodnight.

2677
03:32:18,267 --> 03:32:20,397
Are those two dating?

2678
03:32:21,087 --> 03:32:23,205
They're not together yet,

2679
03:32:23,206 --> 03:32:26,126
but they are testing the waters.

2680
03:32:27,946 --> 03:32:30,625
It's frustrating to watch them.

2681
03:32:30,626 --> 03:32:32,256
Yeongju...

2682
03:32:32,987 --> 03:32:34,416
She's nice.

2683
03:32:34,417 --> 03:32:35,756
She is.

2684
03:32:35,757 --> 03:32:37,945
She's pretty and pleasant.

2685
03:32:37,946 --> 03:32:41,195
And she's a teacher.

2686
03:32:41,196 --> 03:32:42,346
Don't you think they look good together?

2687
03:32:42,347 --> 03:32:44,037
Yes, they do.

2688
03:32:54,487 --> 03:32:55,706
(Unique Spicy Chicken Stew)

2689
03:33:20,056 --> 03:33:22,586
Ms. Kang Yeongju, what's all this?

2690
03:33:22,587 --> 03:33:24,447
Why are you cooking all of a sudden?

2691
03:33:26,136 --> 03:33:27,716
I'm just practicing.

2692
03:33:28,126 --> 03:33:29,667
Practicing?

2693
03:33:33,317 --> 03:33:35,486
Oh, I get it.

2694
03:33:35,487 --> 03:33:36,516
Girl...

2695
03:33:36,517 --> 03:33:39,906
You have a good eye.

2696
03:33:39,907 --> 03:33:40,716
What do you mean?

2697
03:33:40,717 --> 03:33:42,596
Jiwan.

2698
03:33:42,597 --> 03:33:44,277
Who cares about education?

2699
03:33:44,278 --> 03:33:47,775
To me, money trumps everything.

2700
03:33:47,776 --> 03:33:50,776
Stop getting ahead of yourself.

2701
03:33:53,296 --> 03:33:55,135
Seonhui is a decent mother-in-law.

2702
03:33:55,136 --> 03:33:57,416
Eunsu is easy.

2703
03:33:57,417 --> 03:34:00,847
The grandmother-in-law
will become forgetful.

2704
03:34:01,456 --> 03:34:05,396
Haengsuk. She's the one to watch out for.

2705
03:34:05,397 --> 03:34:07,285
I'm sick of your marriage talk.

2706
03:34:07,286 --> 03:34:08,646
I told you it's not like that.

2707
03:34:08,647 --> 03:34:09,517
Just leave me alone.

2708
03:34:09,518 --> 03:34:12,406
How could I leave you alone?

2709
03:34:12,407 --> 03:34:14,055
You won't go on blind dates,

2710
03:34:14,056 --> 03:34:16,386
but you can't even make Jiwan yours.

2711
03:34:17,436 --> 03:34:18,926
If it were me in the old days,

2712
03:34:18,927 --> 03:34:20,847
I would've already...

2713
03:34:21,597 --> 03:34:23,316
What's the use of giving you my looks?

2714
03:34:23,317 --> 03:34:24,965
Just look at yourself.

2715
03:34:24,966 --> 03:34:28,045
You're dressed like a tomboy,

2716
03:34:28,046 --> 03:34:29,926
and you haven't taken a shower.

2717
03:34:29,927 --> 03:34:32,875
You need to make yourself look pretty!

2718
03:34:32,876 --> 03:34:35,566
Practicing cooking won't help you at all.

2719
03:34:35,567 --> 03:34:38,066
If a girl is pretty, nothing else matters.

2720
03:34:38,067 --> 03:34:39,535
You have to look pretty!

2721
03:34:39,536 --> 03:34:41,396
What good will cooking do for you?

2722
03:34:41,397 --> 03:34:42,766
Besides your pretty face,

2723
03:34:42,767 --> 03:34:45,516
you got nothing from me!

2724
03:34:45,517 --> 03:34:47,827
What do you mean? Like this?

2725
03:34:50,786 --> 03:34:51,955
Oh, you're impossible.

2726
03:34:51,956 --> 03:34:54,406
You're my daughter, but you're impossible!

2727
03:34:54,407 --> 03:34:57,277
Be more like Oh Minja! Like me!

2728
03:34:59,856 --> 03:35:00,926
Minja.

2729
03:35:00,927 --> 03:35:01,847
Oh!

2730
03:35:01,847 --> 03:35:02,817
Ms. Lee!

2731
03:35:02,818 --> 03:35:03,865
What are you doing here?

2732
03:35:03,866 --> 03:35:07,166
I need a new pillow for my neck pain.

2733
03:35:07,167 --> 03:35:08,657
What about you?

2734
03:35:09,296 --> 03:35:12,147
Yeongju's been complaining
about neck pain, too.

2735
03:35:13,436 --> 03:35:14,715
Well,

2736
03:35:14,716 --> 03:35:18,327
is Yeongju still going on blind dates?

2737
03:35:19,806 --> 03:35:21,135
I've given up on that.

2738
03:35:21,136 --> 03:35:22,486
How they feel about each
other is important,

2739
03:35:22,487 --> 03:35:24,216
not their background.

2740
03:35:24,667 --> 03:35:27,476
You're right!

2741
03:35:27,477 --> 03:35:32,657
But I heard you hold education very high.

2742
03:35:33,536 --> 03:35:36,826
If they're in love,
education doesn't matter.

2743
03:35:36,827 --> 03:35:39,867
As long as he's hard-working, it's fine.

2744
03:35:40,606 --> 03:35:45,727
But isn't a small family better?

2745
03:35:46,556 --> 03:35:49,896
I would prefer a small family,

2746
03:35:49,897 --> 03:35:51,295
but these days, as complicated as it is,

2747
03:35:51,296 --> 03:35:54,586
people don't live with married children.

2748
03:35:54,587 --> 03:35:57,007
- You mean live separately? / - Yes.

2749
03:35:58,147 --> 03:35:59,705
But that's...

2750
03:35:59,706 --> 03:36:01,545
Well...

2751
03:36:01,546 --> 03:36:03,916
Old people don't live forever.

2752
03:36:03,917 --> 03:36:06,617
And I'm dying to have a great-grandchild.

2753
03:36:07,147 --> 03:36:09,666
I'm not going to let my daughter

2754
03:36:09,667 --> 03:36:11,476
date anyone with a large family.

2755
03:36:11,477 --> 03:36:13,885
What if she gets stuck with them?

2756
03:36:13,886 --> 03:36:15,706
That won't be good.

2757
03:36:17,337 --> 03:36:20,517
Yes, getting stuck is the key.

2758
03:36:20,856 --> 03:36:22,625
As long as they live separately,

2759
03:36:22,626 --> 03:36:25,195
you don't mind a big family?

2760
03:36:25,196 --> 03:36:26,746
Of course not.

2761
03:36:26,747 --> 03:36:29,046
As long as they are in love.

2762
03:36:29,927 --> 03:36:30,817
Why do you ask?

2763
03:36:30,818 --> 03:36:34,605
You have someone in mind?

2764
03:36:34,606 --> 03:36:36,056
Of course.

2765
03:36:37,876 --> 03:36:40,036
- You do? / - Yes.

2766
03:36:51,206 --> 03:36:53,976
Hello, I'm Ha Yeongho from Daehan Daily.

2767
03:36:53,977 --> 03:36:57,736
Someone tipped me off about Taehu Industry.

2768
03:36:57,737 --> 03:37:00,775
You drove Taehu Industry into bankruptcy,

2769
03:37:00,776 --> 03:37:03,986
and stole millions in funds. Is that true?

2770
03:37:03,987 --> 03:37:05,566
There are protocols for reporters...

2771
03:37:05,567 --> 03:37:07,156
Your former employee Lee Seokjin, and

2772
03:37:07,157 --> 03:37:09,875
former directors will be giving statements!

2773
03:37:09,876 --> 03:37:11,266
Tell me if it's true,

2774
03:37:11,267 --> 03:37:13,516
or if it's slander!

2775
03:37:13,517 --> 03:37:16,426
President Jang!

2776
03:37:16,427 --> 03:37:17,547
Please leave.

2777
03:37:20,856 --> 03:37:22,886
Refuse all interviews.

2778
03:37:23,507 --> 03:37:25,047
It wasn't Kim Jiwan.

2779
03:37:25,936 --> 03:37:28,375
Don't jump the gun, or get them involved.

2780
03:37:28,376 --> 03:37:30,417
I'm sure the reporter heard a rumor.

2781
03:37:32,286 --> 03:37:33,516
If he had all the evidence,

2782
03:37:33,517 --> 03:37:35,637
he would've written about it already.

2783
03:37:36,397 --> 03:37:38,885
I'm coming in, so make sure no one talks.

2784
03:37:38,886 --> 03:37:42,236
I told you to find him, by any means!

2785
03:37:42,237 --> 03:37:43,077
What are you doing?

2786
03:37:43,078 --> 03:37:44,907
Is it that you can't or won't?

2787
03:37:47,267 --> 03:37:48,986
Seokjin was

2788
03:37:48,987 --> 03:37:51,726
with us from the birth of Taehu Industry,

2789
03:37:51,727 --> 03:37:53,727
and is still with us today.

2790
03:37:54,806 --> 03:37:58,016
Dongjin still calls us to congratulate us

2791
03:37:58,017 --> 03:38:00,427
whenever we reach a new milestone.

2792
03:38:01,817 --> 03:38:05,676
Hyeokju practically lived with us

2793
03:38:05,677 --> 03:38:07,357
at the factory.

2794
03:38:08,477 --> 03:38:10,935
So how could I

2795
03:38:10,936 --> 03:38:14,346
dig into their past, and make threats?

2796
03:38:15,327 --> 03:38:16,857
Taesu!

2797
03:38:20,286 --> 03:38:22,817
You've been paid off, too?

2798
03:38:25,276 --> 03:38:28,365
I know you met with Seokjin.

2799
03:38:28,366 --> 03:38:30,546
I wasn't sure.

2800
03:38:31,036 --> 03:38:32,355
So, what did you get from them?

2801
03:38:32,356 --> 03:38:35,286
How much did they pay you!

2802
03:38:35,917 --> 03:38:37,305
Taesu...

2803
03:38:37,306 --> 03:38:38,555
Get out.

2804
03:38:38,556 --> 03:38:39,536
You're fired!

2805
03:38:39,537 --> 03:38:40,907
Get lost!

2806
03:39:43,056 --> 03:39:44,706
Hyeondo,

2807
03:39:45,436 --> 03:39:48,166
I once told your father

2808
03:39:48,167 --> 03:39:50,457
to watch his back because of you.

2809
03:39:53,067 --> 03:39:55,446
And he said to me,

2810
03:39:57,106 --> 03:39:59,166
even if you betrayed him, that was okay.

2811
03:40:00,366 --> 03:40:02,346
Because you're his son.

2812
03:40:06,456 --> 03:40:08,477
Look after Taesu.

2813
03:40:10,696 --> 03:40:13,196
I can't seem to do it anymore.

2814
03:41:07,087 --> 03:41:10,435
Is this Mr. Han Yeongho of Daehan Daily?

2815
03:41:10,436 --> 03:41:12,306
This is Kim Jiwan.

2816
03:41:13,536 --> 03:41:16,926
Can we have that interview tomorrow?

2817
03:41:23,997 --> 03:41:25,617
Yes, Mr. Han.

2818
03:41:26,876 --> 03:41:28,556
I'm on my way.

2819
03:42:27,237 --> 03:42:28,796
Your father was going to

2820
03:42:30,007 --> 03:42:33,597
hand over his company to my father?

2821
03:42:36,876 --> 03:42:39,376
I couldn't understand him at first,

2822
03:42:41,657 --> 03:42:44,656
but now that I think about it,

2823
03:42:44,657 --> 03:42:46,587
I can understand him a little bit.

2824
03:43:00,136 --> 03:43:02,257
This is all the evidence I've collected.

2825
03:43:06,616 --> 03:43:08,506
Why are you giving them to me?

2826
03:43:13,647 --> 03:43:15,666
Why did you

2827
03:43:15,667 --> 03:43:17,827
give me that notebook?

2828
03:43:51,227 --> 03:43:52,546
Have you had a lot to drink?

2829
03:43:53,876 --> 03:43:57,397
You asked me here, so why are you late?

2830
03:44:02,017 --> 03:44:03,947
I met Jiwan.

2831
03:44:07,376 --> 03:44:09,657
Uncle Sangjun

2832
03:44:11,337 --> 03:44:14,647
was going to give you all his money?

2833
03:44:15,397 --> 03:44:17,306
That's a lie.

2834
03:44:18,077 --> 03:44:19,997
Right?

2835
03:44:23,456 --> 03:44:26,316
Who would actually do that?

2836
03:44:26,317 --> 03:44:28,646
Why would he give you his company

2837
03:44:28,647 --> 03:44:31,266
when he has a son and a family?

2838
03:44:31,267 --> 03:44:33,187
That's ridiculous.

2839
03:44:33,847 --> 03:44:35,667
You were just a friend.

2840
03:44:36,786 --> 03:44:38,577
Not his blood.

2841
03:44:42,606 --> 03:44:44,516
Don't you agree?

2842
03:44:46,157 --> 03:44:47,737
Yes.

2843
03:44:48,337 --> 03:44:50,317
I'm not his blood.

2844
03:44:53,206 --> 03:44:55,516
But,

2845
03:44:56,347 --> 03:44:59,096
even though I wasn't his blood,

2846
03:44:59,097 --> 03:45:02,736
Sangjun might have actually really

2847
03:45:02,737 --> 03:45:06,886
wanted to give me his company.

2848
03:45:09,876 --> 03:45:13,445
But why...

2849
03:45:13,446 --> 03:45:15,966
How could he trust me so much?

2850
03:45:53,436 --> 03:45:54,676
Jiwan.

2851
03:45:58,077 --> 03:46:01,416
Do you

2852
03:46:01,417 --> 03:46:04,296
remember Dad?

2853
03:46:07,327 --> 03:46:09,187
A little bit.

2854
03:46:12,296 --> 03:46:18,036
What kind of person was he?

2855
03:46:20,917 --> 03:46:24,107
He smiled at me whenever he saw me.

2856
03:46:31,657 --> 03:46:34,216
Why did

2857
03:46:36,087 --> 03:46:40,397
Dad trust a man like him?

2858
03:46:42,587 --> 03:46:45,187
He was so foolish.

2859
03:46:49,657 --> 03:46:52,636
You think so, too, don't you?

2860
03:48:03,337 --> 03:48:04,757
How have you been?

2861
03:48:17,636 --> 03:48:19,706
Don't turn bad.

2862
03:48:22,177 --> 03:48:24,847
That's not who you are, Hyeondo.

2863
03:48:35,776 --> 03:48:37,386
I should go.

2864
03:49:17,397 --> 03:49:18,635
The Korean Businessmen's Association

2865
03:49:18,636 --> 03:49:22,456
recommended you as a next chairperson.

2866
03:49:22,917 --> 03:49:26,847
You're to give an acceptance speech.

2867
03:49:28,296 --> 03:49:29,535
Okay.

2868
03:49:29,536 --> 03:49:31,016
I got it.

2869
03:49:31,597 --> 03:49:33,045
Oh, and

2870
03:49:33,046 --> 03:49:35,146
call my wife's lawyer,

2871
03:49:35,147 --> 03:49:37,166
and have him visit me here.

2872
03:49:37,167 --> 03:49:38,607
Yes, sir.

2873
03:49:46,696 --> 03:49:48,646
President Jang wants to see you

2874
03:49:48,647 --> 03:49:50,526
before going to court.

2875
03:49:51,827 --> 03:49:53,455
What is it about?

2876
03:49:53,456 --> 03:49:56,046
He said he will tell you in person.

2877
03:50:49,536 --> 03:50:52,736
You like the coffee here, don't you?

2878
03:50:52,737 --> 03:50:55,666
You didn't call me here for coffee.

2879
03:50:55,667 --> 03:50:57,667
What is this about?

2880
03:50:58,716 --> 03:51:00,926
I called you over to have a cup of coffee.

2881
03:51:01,776 --> 03:51:03,397
Excuse me.

2882
03:51:25,177 --> 03:51:28,416
I came because you like it here,

2883
03:51:28,417 --> 03:51:30,035
but to me, the company

2884
03:51:30,036 --> 03:51:33,186
vending machine coffee's the best.

2885
03:51:34,407 --> 03:51:38,465
You've always had cheap taste.

2886
03:51:38,466 --> 03:51:39,805
What?

2887
03:51:39,806 --> 03:51:41,987
You hate me because of my cheap taste?

2888
03:51:42,556 --> 03:51:44,935
No,

2889
03:51:44,936 --> 03:51:47,166
it was easy for me.

2890
03:51:49,856 --> 03:51:51,535
Successful men

2891
03:51:51,536 --> 03:51:55,086
always get a mistress first.

2892
03:51:55,087 --> 03:51:57,385
But

2893
03:51:57,386 --> 03:52:00,445
you have simple taste in everything.

2894
03:52:00,446 --> 03:52:02,596
Vending machine coffee, soju,

2895
03:52:02,597 --> 03:52:04,637
and roasted rice tea after meals.

2896
03:52:05,917 --> 03:52:08,507
And with women, only Jeong Sugyeong.

2897
03:52:10,267 --> 03:52:13,455
I did have simple taste,

2898
03:52:13,456 --> 03:52:16,056
but it was never cheap.

2899
03:52:18,946 --> 03:52:23,846
I loved having you

2900
03:52:23,847 --> 03:52:25,637
as my husband.

2901
03:52:28,466 --> 03:52:31,805
I respected you

2902
03:52:31,806 --> 03:52:36,626
more than anyone.

2903
03:52:41,477 --> 03:52:44,545
If you are willing to change,

2904
03:52:44,546 --> 03:52:47,477
nothing will change between us.

2905
03:52:55,497 --> 03:53:00,156
Will Jeong Sugyeong still love Jang Taesu

2906
03:53:00,157 --> 03:53:03,427
without his money and honor?

2907
03:53:07,196 --> 03:53:10,556
That's why it can't be, Ms. Jeong.

2908
03:53:21,456 --> 03:53:23,045
This is the divorce papers.

2909
03:53:23,046 --> 03:53:25,066
I already signed it,

2910
03:53:25,067 --> 03:53:27,097
so you take care of the rest.

2911
03:55:10,626 --> 03:55:13,846
Are you sure you want to let this go?

2912
03:55:14,977 --> 03:55:17,466
You won't regret it?

2913
03:55:19,286 --> 03:55:21,716
That was what Father wanted.

2914
03:55:22,956 --> 03:55:25,236
If President Jang

2915
03:55:25,237 --> 03:55:29,107
doesn't change his ways after finding out

2916
03:55:30,007 --> 03:55:32,707
what Father wanted, he'll
be more miserable.

2917
03:55:53,026 --> 03:55:56,166
Hello, everyone.

2918
03:55:56,167 --> 03:55:58,676
I'm Jang Taesu from Best Global,

2919
03:55:58,677 --> 03:56:02,117
who recently won Businessman of the Year.

2920
03:56:08,067 --> 03:56:11,965
There are many senior entrepreneurs

2921
03:56:11,966 --> 03:56:13,775
and colleagues who deserve the award,

2922
03:56:13,776 --> 03:56:15,506
so I feel a very big responsibility

2923
03:56:15,507 --> 03:56:17,747
to win this accolade.

2924
03:56:18,186 --> 03:56:22,855
And it's an honor to have the position

2925
03:56:22,856 --> 03:56:25,856
to represent all entrepreneurs.

2926
03:56:27,257 --> 03:56:31,066
Sitting here

2927
03:56:31,067 --> 03:56:33,677
brings back old memories.

2928
03:56:36,446 --> 03:56:41,886
I had a friend.

2929
03:56:42,477 --> 03:56:46,445
He trusted me when I had nothing,

2930
03:56:46,446 --> 03:56:51,026
and helped me get to where I am today.

2931
03:56:51,626 --> 03:56:53,846
He was the president of Taehu Industry

2932
03:56:53,847 --> 03:56:56,947
where Best Global began.

2933
03:57:00,327 --> 03:57:02,727
Kim Sangjun.

2934
03:57:04,667 --> 03:57:08,437
That was my friend's name.

2935
03:57:09,056 --> 03:57:12,375
He was naively trusting,

2936
03:57:12,376 --> 03:57:14,855
and honest

2937
03:57:14,856 --> 03:57:18,526
even to a fault.

2938
03:57:19,856 --> 03:57:22,596
I considered his company

2939
03:57:22,597 --> 03:57:26,047
as my own,

2940
03:57:27,366 --> 03:57:30,296
and worked hard.

2941
03:57:38,136 --> 03:57:41,396
But,

2942
03:57:41,397 --> 03:57:45,445
I

2943
03:57:45,446 --> 03:57:48,567
Stole...

2944
03:58:01,286 --> 03:58:03,706
All of his money.

2945
03:58:06,606 --> 03:58:08,076
What did he just say?

2946
03:58:26,356 --> 03:58:30,096
Yeongju, summarize this register, please.

2947
03:58:32,046 --> 03:58:33,667
May I help you?

2948
03:58:37,526 --> 03:58:39,715
Mr. Jang Hyeondo.

2949
03:58:39,716 --> 03:58:42,456
How dare you come here!

2950
03:58:43,546 --> 03:58:45,276
Jang Hyeondo?

2951
03:58:46,157 --> 03:58:48,256
You're that guy?

2952
03:58:48,257 --> 03:58:49,596
How dare you show your face here?

2953
03:58:49,597 --> 03:58:51,287
Get out.

2954
03:59:04,686 --> 03:59:06,876
I'm sorry.

2955
03:59:08,106 --> 03:59:11,336
That's all I can say.

2956
03:59:21,487 --> 03:59:23,027
Yes.

2957
03:59:23,917 --> 03:59:29,465
I tricked my trusting friend's family,

2958
03:59:29,466 --> 03:59:33,086
and bought their shares for pennies.

2959
03:59:33,087 --> 03:59:37,465
And I even kicked his family out

2960
03:59:37,466 --> 03:59:40,397
from their house.

2961
03:59:44,487 --> 03:59:47,226
And so I used

2962
03:59:47,227 --> 03:59:51,296
the stolen money,

2963
03:59:53,257 --> 03:59:57,427
and built my own company.

2964
04:00:08,216 --> 04:00:10,376
(Taehu Industry Stock
Certificate, $2.5 Million)

2965
04:00:51,417 --> 04:00:52,847
Dad!

2966
04:02:13,556 --> 04:02:16,516
(KBS 2TV, Weekend Drama, Bluebird's House)

2967
04:02:16,517 --> 04:02:17,465
I knew then,

2968
04:02:17,466 --> 04:02:18,397
(Best Global's Jang Taesu
Confesses to Embezzlement)

2969
04:02:18,786 --> 04:02:22,795
I would regret it for the rest of my life.

2970
04:02:22,796 --> 04:02:25,256
Sangjun

2971
04:02:25,257 --> 04:02:28,147
might have died because of me.

2972
04:02:29,347 --> 04:02:31,326
He's giving you what?

2973
04:02:31,327 --> 04:02:32,506
Stocks.

2974
04:02:32,507 --> 04:02:35,647
And he's resigning from his position.

2975
04:02:36,477 --> 04:02:39,435
Why are they so dense,

2976
04:02:39,436 --> 04:02:40,586
when I'm trying to help them?

2977
04:02:40,587 --> 04:02:42,596
They should at least try to

2978
04:02:42,597 --> 04:02:43,945
go on a few dates.

2979
04:02:43,946 --> 04:02:46,115
You're going to let Father be as he is?

2980
04:02:46,116 --> 04:02:49,356
Ma'am, get me a glass of ice water!

